BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Alibi LGBTQ April Book Club: Mona of the Manor by Armistead Maupin
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T173000
UID:260328ikKxkw7e8EuLXklhiikHxQ
DESCRIPTION:Please join us to discuss the delightful “Mona of the Manor\
 ,” the last installment of Armistead Maupin’s classic “Tales of the 
 City” series hosted by Richard May!\n\nSet in the early 1990s\, the long
 -awaited tenth novel in Armistead Maupin’s beloved found family saga\, t
 he Tales of the City series\, follows the adventures of Mona Ramsey\, now 
 the widowed Lady of a glorious old manor in Britain’s golden Cotswolds\,
  and her fabulous adopted son Wilfred\, as they come to the aid of an Amer
 ican visitor with a troubling secret.\n\nWhen Mona Ramsey married Lord Ted
 dy Roughton to secure his visa—allowing him to remain in San Francisco t
 o fulfill his wildest dreams—she never imagined she would\, by age 48\, 
 be the sole owner of Easley House\, Teddy’s grand\, romantic British cou
 ntry manor in the UK. She also didn't imagine that she’d need to open th
 e manor’s doors to paying guests to afford the electric bill and repair 
 the leaking roof. Yet somehow she and her young friend Wilfred—whom gues
 ts assume is serving as Easley’s charming-but-clumsy butler—and the lo
 opy old gardener Mr. Hargis\, are making it work.\n\nThis delicate equilib
 rium is upended when Americans Rhonda and Ernie Blaylock arrive for a week
 end vacation at Easley\, and Wilfred stumbles onto their terrible secret. 
 Now\, instead of being able to focus on the imminent arrival of her old fr
 iend Michael Tolliver and beloved parent Anna Madrigal\, Mona will need to
  focus all of her considerable charm\, willpower\, and wiles—and the hel
 p of Wilfred and Mona’s girlfriend Poppy\, the town’s postmistress and
  local calligraphy whiz—to set things right before the Midsummer ceremon
 y when the whole town will descend on Easley’s historic grounds.
LOCATION:Alibi Bookshop
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1290813059644287
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
