SUMMARY:Drawing in Joy: Laughing with Life\, a Dance on Paper
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T200000
UID:260324n40vnxUwykWWGnh_0rF4vw
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nThursdays\, April 9 – 30\, 2026 5:30 PM – 8:00
  PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Cat
 egories: Drawing & Painting\, Extended Classes\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and old
 er\n\nRegistration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nMaterials Fee:\n\nSee Required List\n\
 nTotal Registration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nExpress joy through drawing. Build sk
 ills in sketching\, composition & landscapes. Boost focus\, creativity\, c
 onnection & well-being.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nWhen we feel a sense of joy\
 , it is natural to express that feeling from our body. We may use our voic
 e and sing\, we may dance\, and we may use our hands in creative expressio
 n. By drawing we leave a mark of that expression. This course is shaped wi
 th skill building exercises to improve eye-hand coordination with quick sk
 etching and gesture drawing and practices of learning to see how to abstra
 ct shapes of light and dark for developing strong compositions. We will fo
 cus on landscape imagery from photos and drawing from setups in the studio
 . Drawing outside of class will be encouraged but not required. There are 
 many health benefits from drawing such as: improvements in cognitive focus
 \, freedom of expression with your hands\, the satisfaction that comes fro
 m seeing the world in a different way\, the social camaraderie of acceptan
 ce in the studio\, and the joy of doing something with your hands.\n\nRequ
 ired Materials List\n\nA good size sketch book for multimedia\n\nNewsprint
  drawing pad \\(12” x 18” or 18” x 24”\\)\n\nBlack pencils\, 6B so
 ft\n\nCompressed charcoal sticks\, black and white\n\nEraser\, kneaded rub
 ber\n\nEraser\, white vinyl\n\nBlack felt pens
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/drawing-in-joy/
