UID:260228xqYa9XxoGEmLDYYY77jt4w
DESCRIPTION:Super Diamond\, featuring Surreal Neil\n\nAn uncanny tribute t
 o beloved\, master singer/songwriter/performer\, American pop icon Neil Di
 amond - has appeared on The Late Show with David Letterman\, CNN\, VH1\, C
 omedy Central and has been featured in publications like Rolling Stone Mag
 azine\, Spin and The New York Times. San Francisco's Super Diamond has bec
 ome one of the most popular live shows at major nightclubs\, theaters\, ba
 llrooms and public events throughout the United States. For three decades 
 the band has performed sell-out shows at venues such as Irving Plaza in Ne
 w York\, 930 Club in Washington D.C.\, Bimbo's in San Francisco\, and Hous
 e of Blues venues in Chicago\, Los Angeles\, San Diego\, Cleveland\, Las V
 egas\, New Orleans and Dallas to name a few.\n\nSuper Diamond delivers a g
 littering\, smoke-filled show performing Neil Diamond's hits with a rock e
 dge and unrestrained enthusiasm.\n\nPure entertainment - classic music com
 bined with fun\,energy and passion! Neil Diamond himself has sung his song
 s on stage with Super Diamond at their shows. Don't let anyone tell you Ne
 il Diamond doesn't "ROCK!"
LOCATION:Coyote Sonoma
URL:https://shop.coyotesonoma.com/super-diamond---the-neil-diamond-tribute
 -410-p210.aspx
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Callie Watts
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T000000
UID:260227Z0orOnve1kKTLJAtapeLfQ
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:4th Street cellars
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107647212?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
