DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T203000
UID:26031936ETRuGHfEWvLDomTZPdkg
DESCRIPTION:Ready to step up your salsa game? Salsa – partner dancing cl
 ass build on the basics\, introducing exciting new turns\, footwork\, and 
 partner patterns to elevate your dancing.\n\nMust have intermediate steps 
 in place\n\nProficiency in lead/follow & turns\n\nProficiency in timing & 
 partnership\n\nNo partner necessary\n\nThis class is designed for dancers 
 who have a solid foundation in salsa fundamentals and are ready to take th
 eir skills to the social dance floor. Moving beyond basic steps and patter
 ns\, we’ll focus on the essential techniques\, musicality\, and partner-
 work dynamics that make for confident and enjoyable social dancing. Drop-i
 n fee is $20 and no partner is required.\n\nDate & Time: Fridays @ 7:30PM 
 – 8:30PM\n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafael\, CA\n\nNote: 
 Arrive 10 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allowed.
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 San Rafael
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/salsa-partner-dancing/1
 7624478/2026-04-10T19
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Brandlin Estate Wine & Food Tasting Experience
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T160000
UID:260312jeifQhmGLUi7nhu6Y0gjaw
DESCRIPTION:Born on the rugged slopes of Mount Veeder\, Brandlin Estate pr
 oduces wines of structure\, intensity\, and place. The Brandlin Experience
  offers an in-depth exploration of this historic vineyard site through a c
 urated tasting of five estate-grown wines—including Zinfandel from centu
 ry-old vines and the estate’s signature Cabernet Sauvignon. This seated\
 , guided experience invites guests to delve into the mountain terroir thro
 ugh the lens of small-lot winemaking. Each wine reflects the elevation\, e
 xposure\, and rocky soils that define the Brandlin Estate. For an added di
 mension\, guests may opt to include seasonal bites\, thoughtfully paired t
 o complement the structure and complexity of the wines. This experience is
  hosted at the picturesque Boathouse.
LOCATION:Brandlin Estate 
URL:https://www.exploretock.com/brandlinestate/experience/565565/the-brand
 lin-wine-food-tasting-experience?date=2026-03-12&size=2&time=10%3A00
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
