DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T150000
UID:260330J12ThADs_k23GFU0rEB2Iw
DESCRIPTION:This joyous\, daylong event at NorCal Public Media brings toge
 ther families\, community partners\, and dynamic literacy advocates — fr
 om beloved PBS characters to nationally recognized authors — for a joyfu
 l\, inclusive literacy experience with more than 15 activities for childr
 en. Literacy Promise partners will be on hand to connect families with res
 ources and tips for promoting reading at home.\n\nSome of the highlights b
 eing planned include:\n\n\\*Buddy the Dinosaur and Carl the Collector from
  PBS Kids\n\n\\*Otto the Otter from the Sonoma County Library\n\n\\*Litera
 cy Quest for the Great Scholastic Book treasure chest \\(free books while 
 supplies last\\)\n\n\\*Live story times with special guest readers\n\n\\*B
 ook signings by authors including Matthew Gollub and Marissa McGee\n\n\\*
 “On air” and “green screen” experiences in the KRCB studios make c
 hildren the stars of radio- and video-style segments\n\n\\*Visit a firetr
 uck and crew from Rohnert Park Department of Public Safety Fire\n\n\\*Food
  available for purchase from local food trucks Sol Azteca\, World Famous C
 orndogs\, and Kona Ice\n\n\\*Engaging literacy experiences hosted by the
  Sonoma County Literacy Promise partners\n\nAnd so much more!
LOCATION:Nor-Cal Public Media
URL:https://www.scoe.org/adventure
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
