BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pasta Machine Printing Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T160000
UID:260216qIxM88X6CEOx8OwVUgTrKg
DESCRIPTION:Revive your manual pasta maker by learning how to use it to cr
 eate small drypoint prints. This technique uses the pressure that normally
  rolls out the pasta dough to print artwork.\n\nStudents will learn how t
 o use different materials to create a plate including milk cartons\, Tetra
  Paks\, and Akua plate material. They'll learn how to ink up the plate\, a
 dd packing to the pasta maker for the perfect impression\, and pull prints
  to make a small edition.\n\nThe small-format prints created in class will
  be up to 4” by 6”. Prints will be made using a drypoint needle and a 
 cutting knife and will be printed on different kinds of print making paper
 . \n\n\\*The pasta machine does not get any ink on it\, so using it for p
 asta AND printing is perfectly fine. Oil based etching ink will be used du
 ring class\; the instructor will demonstrate how easy it is to clean up wi
 thout any heavy cleaning solution.\n\n*The materials fee includes a drypoi
 nt needle\, as printing paper\, plate material.*
LOCATION:North Bay Letterpress Arts
URL:https://www.northbayletterpressarts.org/for-sale/2026-pasta
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
