DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSunday\, April 12\, 2026 2:00 PM – 5:00 PM\n\nLo
 cation\n\nRoom 200\, Sam Morphy Community Room\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll 
 Levels\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\nRegistration Cost:\n\n$45\n\nOne-d
 ay deep dive into shaping what you truly want into a clear\, creative visi
 on.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nEver feel like you have an idea of the creative
  path your want to follow — but when it comes time to actually go for it
 \, things get fuzzy? This workshop is here to fix that. In one focused day
 \, you’ll dig deep\, cut through the noise\, and walk away with a crysta
 l-clear vision for your creative life — one that’s exciting\, grounded
 \, and actually yours. No vague daydreaming here. We’re talking about s
 haping your big ideas into a real\, actionable direction you can build on.
  Whether you’re just starting out or you’ve been making art for years\
 , this is your space to get honest about what you truly want — and final
 ly give it a shape. Come as you are. Leave with clarity. Open to artists a
 t every stage of the journey.\n\nListen to Yohki on KSVY!
