BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What to do When a Big One Hits - an Earthquake Tabletop Exercise
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T143000
UID:2604072_HioZSrrUiEjYSqV1-_Jg
DESCRIPTION:Want to know what to do after a strong earthquake hits and fir
 st responders cannot help and you cannot get out? During this free worksho
 p\, you and the “neighbors” at your table will walk through steps on h
 ow you will collectively survive the week following a 6.8M earthquake. How
  do you check on neighbors safely? Do you have sufficient food and water? 
 What will you do if someone needs medical help? What are the potential saf
 ety issues?\n\nThere is limited seating for this event so register early a
 t bit.ly/EQTabletop or call the senior center at 707-838-1260. Dr Nancy Br
 own with the Sonoma County Dept of Emergency Management will assist with t
 he exercise\, which is open to all adults in Sonoma County. Pre-registrati
 on is required. This presentation is part of the Windsor Ready Talk series
  hosted by the Town of Windsor and Windsor COPE. For more information emai
 l windsor\\_cope@yahoo.com.
LOCATION:Windsor Senior Center
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/what-to-do-when-a-big-o
 ne-hits-an-earthquake-tabletop-exercise/18520175/2026-04-14T13
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
