BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Family Art Lab
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T151500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T170000
UID:260401uAQvnYBmH0-cFNOWbCe5Xg
DESCRIPTION:4 - 18\\+ yrs Adult participation optional Class Experience To
 gether\, we will breathe and enjoy the feel of our hands creating with col
 orful textural materials. This class is designed for littles ones and thei
 r families to unwind and decompress in the late afternoon and enjoy proces
 s art. We will create with a variety of materials that will be set out in 
 an open ended\, Reggio Emelia style where students are offered invitations
  to play with the materials. We will explore different themes such as pain
 ting with acrylic or tempera\; do collages with various types of paper and
  mixed media\; practice sculpture\; or just make creative art with recycle
 d materials. The only assignment is to play and explore with colors\, shap
 es\, and textures\, with no messy clean-up at home! "Play is a key compone
 nt of the arts and aesthetics in myriad ways. Art and play are like two si
 des of the same coin\, with play being a part of artistic expression\, ima
 gination\, creativity\, and curiosity." - Susan Magsamen\,  Your Brain on 
 Art: How the Arts Transform Us Amanda Rose Hopkins has a Bachelor of Fine 
 Arts from UC Santa Cruz and thereafter she worked as an apprentice artist 
 at the Sarnath International Nyingma Institute\, near Varanasi\, India. Sh
 e has been working with children since 2009. She completed a multiple subj
 ect teaching credential program and has worked locally at Sunridge Charter
  School\, The REACH School\, Sebastopol Center for the Arts and Santa Rosa
  Junior College. She has studied multicultural education\, Positive Discip
 line\, Toolbox and child development. Notes Land of the Good Members get 2
 0% \\(!\\) off this class using code: 2026member To utilize the discount\,
  please first activate a membership or email us at hello@landofthegood.com
  if you need help subscribing! Class Requirements Students need to be full
 y potty-trained and able to communicate/navigate self-care needs. What you
 'll learn Students will be exposed to methods of painting Various types of
  paintbrushes Acrylic painting Tempera painting Oil pastel drawing Collage
  Types of adhesives and their uses Sculptural techniques Recycled art Samp
 le Class Format 3:15pm - 5:00pm\; late drop-off or early pick-up are fine 
 as this is an open-art lab and children may have varying capacity. Parents
  or other supervising adults are welcome to stay and participate or enjoy 
 tea & coffee and use the high-speed internet/cowork during class time. Ple
 ase pick up promptly by 5pm. Other Things To Know Adult Participation Opti
 onal. One adult View more
LOCATION:Santa Rosa Junior College
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/family-art-lab/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Brandlin Estate Wine & Food Tasting Experience
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260415T160000
UID:260312C0_DSjjvXkKyyVKRNVkfVQ
DESCRIPTION:Born on the rugged slopes of Mount Veeder\, Brandlin Estate pr
 oduces wines of structure\, intensity\, and place. The Brandlin Experience
  offers an in-depth exploration of this historic vineyard site through a c
 urated tasting of five estate-grown wines—including Zinfandel from centu
 ry-old vines and the estate’s signature Cabernet Sauvignon. This seated\
 , guided experience invites guests to delve into the mountain terroir thro
 ugh the lens of small-lot winemaking. Each wine reflects the elevation\, e
 xposure\, and rocky soils that define the Brandlin Estate. For an added di
 mension\, guests may opt to include seasonal bites\, thoughtfully paired t
 o complement the structure and complexity of the wines. This experience is
  hosted at the picturesque Boathouse.
LOCATION:Brandlin Estate 
URL:https://www.exploretock.com/brandlinestate/experience/565565/the-brand
 lin-wine-food-tasting-experience?date=2026-03-12&size=2&time=10%3A00
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
