BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pizza-Making Class with Chef Bryan Jones\, supporting Sonoma Famil
 y Meal
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T193000
UID:260408StOFngqHNUSzoBXGc0Xa9Q
DESCRIPTION:Craft Pizza-Making Class with Chef Bryan Jones - April 16\n\n$
 100.00\n\nWe’re finally bringing pizza to the Sonoma Family Meal kitchen
 ! Join us and chef Bryan Jones for a cooking class on Thursday\, April 16t
 h to learn how to perfect the art of scratch pizza dough\, marinara\, and 
 mouthwatering toppings to satisfy all your senses.\n\nThe hands-on\, colla
 borative class will last 2.5 hours\, with time to enjoy your meal together
  at the end. Whether you’re a seasoned cook or just starting out\, this 
 class will offer a fun\, engaging learning environment\, while raising fun
 ds for Sonoma Family Meal’s free culinary job training and food-security
  programs.\n\nIf you haven’t been to the SFM Kitchen yet\, this class is
  also the perfect chance to visit and experience where the magic takes pla
 ce and how the work gets done.\n\nWHEN: Thursday April 16th\, 5-7:30pm WHE
 RE: SFM community kitchen\, 1370A Redwood Way\, Petaluma\n\nTHE MENU:\n\nS
 cratch Pizza Dough\n\nScratch Marinara Sauce\n\nMargherita Pizza\n\nHot Ho
 ney & Pepperoni Pizza\n\nBig Seasonal Salad will be served\n\nBYOB: Bring 
 Your Own Beverage\n\nIf you have a specific food allergy or have any quest
 ions about the menu\, please contact hannah@sonomafamilymeal.org.\n\nABOUT
  THE CHEF:\n\nBryan Jones takes the art of restaurant quality cuisine outs
 ide of the traditional restaurant kitchen and into evocative local spaces 
 and intimate environments. Offering boutique catering and private chef ser
 vices\, Bryan offers a culinary experience that’s creative\, custom and 
 designed from scratch for each menu and every singular occasion. \n\nAs a
  graduate of the California Culinary Academy in San Francisco\, Bryan brin
 gs over 20 years of experience in the kitchen to his craft. His approach t
 o food reflects a diverse restaurants background\, showcasing bold\, clean
  flavors and influences from a variety of cultures. \n\nAs the Executive 
 Chef at St. Francis Winery\, Bryan was the creative force behind the highl
 y rated food and wine pairing program at the winery\, where it was Zagat r
 ecommended and voted \\#1 restaurant by OpenTable diners in 2013 and 2015.
  He joined St. Francis winery in 2014 after ten years as Chef and General 
 Manager of the fig cafe and wine bar\, the sister restaurant of the girl a
 nd the fig. He has cooked in locations around the world\, including Garmis
 ch\, Germany\, Vail\, Colorado\, Santa Fe\, New Mexico and many other loca
 tions throughout the Bay Area. \n\nBryan uses this culinary history—and
  a natural curiosity for how experiences translate onto the palette—to c
 reate one-of-a-kind experiences in unique locations and private homes acro
 ss Wine Country\, and beyond.
LOCATION:Sonoma Family Meal Community Kitchen
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/pizza-making-class-with
 -chef-bryan-jones-supporting-sonoma-family-meal/18357393/2026-04-16T17
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kearsley Home Furnishings Moving Sale
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T173000
UID:260406Gz7c5sZ2LkCechMn2sTtKQ
DESCRIPTION:Kearsley\, Sonoma’s renowned luxury linen and textile atelie
 r\, is relocating. In preparation\, the atelier has released its Kearsley 
 and Barbara Beckmann inventory at rare\, decisive pricing\, beginning at 5
 0% off.\n\nThe sale includes in-stock bed linens\, duvet covers\, coverlet
 s\, sheets\, pillowcases\, shams\, and outdoor pillows\, as well as fine f
 abrics by the yard for upholstery and drapery. Also available are hotel sa
 mple robes\, antique furniture\, a sleigh bed\, original artwork\, and rar
 e textile pieces seldom offered to the public.\n\nA broader selection is a
 vailable in-store\, including one-of-a-kind furnishings and collector-leve
 l pieces not listed online.\n\nKearsley is located through the Orchard Pla
 ce driveway entrance at Winery Sixteen 600\, and can also be accessed dire
 ctly from First Street West. The atelier is situated upstairs\, in the bac
