BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:INTO THE LIGHT: Light-filled aintings by Katy Boggs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T170000
UID:260330RiAQwZbX2USWlSwIzaqRog
DESCRIPTION:Katy's paintings are an exploration of light—how it shapes f
 orm\, reveals color\, and defines what we see.\n\n"I am drawn to moments w
 here light is felt as much as seen: filtering through dense leaves\, tower
 ing in the crowns of trees\, glinting off cresting waves\, or softening in
 to the quiet glow of a sunset. Light is everywhere\; without it\, there is
  no seeing. Beyond its physical presence\, it also carries a deeper resona
 nce as a symbol of hope. In a time of uncertainty\, this work seeks to bri
 ng light into the image\, both visually and metaphorically."\n\nReception:
  April 25\, 4 to 6 pm.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Gallery
URL:http://sebastopolgallery.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Photographing Your Roses
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T200000
UID:260330PgHOhKM3yEy7QeS93YGTJw
DESCRIPTION:Presented by Betty Mott\, Master Rosarian. Betty will share si
 mple techniques for capturing the beauty of roses\, printing your images a
 nd framing them\, and how to best style and shoot your blooms. For those w
 anting to enter your rose pictures into the Spring Rose Show\, Betty will 
 offer valuable tips on how to present award-winning rose photography that 
 will catch a judge's eye!\n\nWhat to bring: One or two 8x10 glossy prints.
  You will be given a free photo mat\, backing and protective sleeve for ea
 ch photo. Betty will demonstrate how to mount a photo to best show off you
 r artistry.\n\nAbout Betty Mott: An active member of the Marin Rose Societ
 y and Santa Clarita Rose Society\, Betty is an ARS Horticulture Judge\, Ph
 otography Judge\, Master Rosarian and ARS Bronze Honor Medal recipient. At
  the District level\, Betty has served in a wide variety of positions incl
 uding Secretary\, Program and Speakers Chair\, member of the Bylaws Revisi
 on Committee and her current role as Photography Judges Chair.\n\n"Roses h
 ave always been a part of my life. Growing up in New England learning from
  my Dad's organic gardening practices helped grow my love for nature\, whi
 ch fueled my passion for photography. One of my great joys is photographin
 g roses outside with natural lighting to tell a story that brings you back
  again and again to gaze upon the image with wonder."--Betty Mott
LOCATION:Luther Burbank Art & Garden Center
URL:https://www.sonomaroses.org/programs
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Solano Mix: Talent Buying\, Staffing & Stronger Events
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T203000
UID:260328gK5OU3JPGUWqnHQRonlSVQ
DESCRIPTION:The Solano Mix is a gathering for people who create experience
 s\, build community\, and make events happen. FREE DINNER AND MIXER! ONLY 
 60 SEATS\n\nThis spring edition focuses on two big ingredients behind succ
 essful events:\n\nTalent buying and how booking has changed in the Bay Are
 a\n\nStaffing and how to build a team that brings energy\, professionalism
 \, and heart\n\nJoin event producers\, venue operators\, artists\, hospita
 lity leaders\, sponsors\, labor resources\, and local businesses for an ev
 ening of insight\, connection\, music\, and good conversation.\n\nWhether 
 you produce festivals\, concerts\, community events\, fundraisers\, market
 s\, or private events\, this mixer is designed to bring useful ideas and r
 eal relationships into the same room.\n\nWhat to expect\n\nNetworking with
  local event professionals and vendors\n\nSpeaker conversation on how tale
 nt buying has changed\n\nInsight from today’s booking world and current 
 realities\n\nDiscussion around hiring and keeping great event staff\n\nLig
 ht mixer atmosphere with music\, conversation\, and community\n\nFree dinn
 er\n\nInspiration\, collaboration\, and practical takeaways\n\nFeatured co
 nversation\n\nThis edition of Solano Mix will explore:\n\nTalent Buying Th
 en & Now\n\nA look at how booking talent has evolved in the Bay Area\, wha
 t has changed\, what still matters\, and how event producers can adapt.\n\
 nHiring Staff Who Elevate the Event\n\nGreat events are not built by logis
 tics alone. They are shaped by people. We’ll talk about how to identify 
 strong staff\, create better team culture\, and hire people who help your 
 event feel organized\, welcoming\, and memorable.
LOCATION:Suite Treatments
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/the-solano-mix-talent-b
 uying-staffing-stronger-events/18445504/2026-04-16T17
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
