DESCRIPTION:Chicky & Dumplins\n\nApril 2\, 2026\, 6 to 9 pm\n\nJoin James 
 Beard Award-winning cookbook author Sarah Owens for a night of making lusc
 ious Chicken n' Dumplings with sourdough starter. If you've been looking f
 or ways to use your starter besides baking\, this is for you! Sarah will s
 how you how to make an unconventional roux and light and fluffy dumplings\
 , both with sourdough starter\, for a fun spin on this classic Southern co
 mfort food. To conclude the evening\, you will enjoy a sit-down meal of a 
 small appetizer\, chicken and dumplings\, salad\, and a light dessert. The
  chicken and dumplings include dairy and meat. One glass of locally produc
 ed wine or NA beverage is included. \n\nGalette Night\n\nApril 16\, 2026 
 6 to 9 pm\n\nJoin James Beard Award-winning cookbook author Sarah Owens fo
 r a night of galette making using a wholegrain sourdough pie crust. If you
 've been looking for ways to use your sourdough starter besides bread\, th
 is is for you! Sarah will show you how to roll out and fill a flaky\, whol
 esome pie crust made with spelt and sourdough starter\, perfect for both s
 weet and savory fillings. While the galettes are baking\, Sarah will demon
 strate how to mix the pie crust and provide you with a recipe to make at h
 ome. To conclude the evening\, you will enjoy a sit-down meal of soup\, a 
 savory galette\, salad\, and a light dessert. The soup and galette are veg
 etarian\, but both include dairy. One glass of locally produced wine or NA
  beverage is included.
LOCATION:Drewish Deli
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/sourdough-supper-club/1
 8370690/2026-04-16T18
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T180000
UID:260318UrNkb1rUbEy5w7y3sYvFBA
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\n**APRIL EXHIBIT: THE 
 POETIC LANDSCAPE**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\n*
 *RECEPTION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILL
 ER and PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by f
 eatured guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.
   Be sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beau
 tiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**\n\nSonoma
  County artist\, **Karen Miller\,** presents **The Poetic Landscape\,** pa
 stel paintings that convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting wi
 th the intrinsic beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid
  shapes and rhythmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true
  poetic interlude.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,”
  turning to the sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the
  river’s edge\, concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing
  in “Fetch.”  The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a 
 shaded secret spot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\,
  these works truly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Mill
 er remarked “ As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surroundin
 g us\, I try to express my painterly response in hopes it will engender re
 cognition by the viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting 
 the Gallery on March 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stai
 rway Smallworks Showcase features **Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\,** a c
 ollection of watercolors that create an atmosphere that is both introspect
 ive and magical.  Familiar domestic scenes are transformed as humans inte
 ract with animals and birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” 
 the red-headed young woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahe
 ad\, flanked by her avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like 
 taking a mini-step on the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nM
 eet the artist: Rapp will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 
 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nAlso join us for **ART NITE HEALDSBURG**\, Thursday\
 , April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.  The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets
  to Art.  ART NITE Healdsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is
  a community event celebrating art and creativity with over 20 galleries p
 articipating.  ArtNiteHealdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Cente
 r Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 
 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further information: Con
 tact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:What About Age? Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T180000
UID:260318Eed9wDvMh0SgFDAkQwfcYg
DESCRIPTION:*What About Age?* art exhibit has arrived in Marin County! Or
 iginally displayed at NYU’s Kimmel Windows\, this exhibit explores ageis
 m through contemporary art\, featuring works by both local youth and senio
 r artists.\n\n*What About Age?* is an art exhibit and educational initiat
 ive designed to challenge stereotypes about aging\, address ageism and soc
 ial isolation\, and promote intergenerational dialogue through the lens of
  art.\n\nIn partnership with Youth in Arts\, the exhibit features artworks
  by local youth and senior artists\, showcasing how age intersects with cr
 eativity\, identity\, and experience. Under the guidance of Youth in Arts\
 , these emerging and established artists work side by side to create colla
 borative pieces\, fostering meaningful connections between generations and
  reflecting the exhibit’s core message: art is ageless.\n\nThe exhibit a
 lso includes artwork panels by New York-based writer and illustrator Aubre
 y Hirsch\, first displayed at NYU’s Kimmel Windows and originally organi
 zed by Stacey Gordon\, NYU’s Program Director of Next Phase Adult Caregi
 ving and Retirement at Work Life.\n\nThe new exhibition will be on view at
  the Marin County Civic Center galleries from January 26 to May 6\, 2026. 
 Works will be displayed on the first and third floor exhibits\, Monday to 
 Friday from 9 a.m. to 6 p.m.\n\nThe *What About Age?* art exhibit is prese
 nted by Marin Cultural Association in partnership with Marin Community Fou
 ndation and Youth in Arts. Beyond the art exhibit\, the *What About Age?* 
 initiative offers programming\, led by Vivalon\, designed to challenge age
 ism and provide resources for Marin County's growing aging population.
LOCATION:Marin County Civic Center
URL:https://www.marincultural.org/exhibitions
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Samba no Pé - First Class
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T193000
UID:260317JdbKLTKuNkCEK-vhVrcc-Q
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to feel the rhythm and energy of Rio de Janeiro! Sa
 mba no Pé \\(Samba in the Foot\\) is the captivating solo style of samba
  danced in the streets and at Carnival\, known for its rapid\, intricate f
 ootwork and infectious hip movements.\n\nYou will learn\n\nThe Basic Step:
  You will master the signature quick-quick-slow rhythm that defines Samba 
 no Pé.\n\nArm & Hip Styling: You will learn how to add the authentic flai
 r\, movement\, and energy that makes Brazilian samba so captivating.\n\nTe
 chnique & Posture: You will receive tips on proper body alignment to help 
 you dance longer\, faster\, and more safely.\n\nRhythm & Musicality: You w
 ill learn how to connect your movement directly to the irresistible beat o
 f the bateria \\(the samba drum section\\).\n\nThis class is perfect for a
 nyone looking to connect with the vibrant spirit of Brazil\, improve coord
 ination\, and get a fantastic workout—all while learning the foundationa
 l steps of this iconic dance. No partner or prior dance experience is requ
 ired! Just bring your enthusiasm and comfortable shoes!\n\nDate & Time: Th
 ursdays @6:30PM – 7:30PM\n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafae
 l\, CA\n\nNote: Arrive 10 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allo
 wed.
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 • San Rafael
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/samba-no-pe
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
