UID:260225A9rTok2XBkKexb_1KcPxiA
DESCRIPTION:An advance directive is an important document for all adults a
 ge 18 and older. It helps you share your healthcare wishes and name someon
 e you trust to make medical decisions for you if you’re ever unable to s
 peak for yourself.\n\nAt these workshops\, we will explain what an advance
  directive is and provide you with help to complete the form.\n\nFree Nota
 ry Public services will be available to get your advance directive documen
 t notarized at no cost to you. Please bring a valid photo ID \\(driver’s
  license or passport\\) if you plan to have your document notarized.\n\nSp
 anish interpreters will be available at both workshops.\n\nJoin us on eith
 er April 16 or April 28 and give your loved ones the peace of mind that co
 mes from knowing your healthcare wishes in advance.\n\nEvent provided by t
 he Providence Sonoma County Inpatient Palliative Care Team.
LOCATION:Providence Santa Rosa Memorial Hospital
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/free-advance-directive-
 health-care-planning-workshop/18185933/2026-04-16T12
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
