DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260417T160000
UID:26032528PG9esXNUGbHVn_J1R_OQ
DESCRIPTION:The Frank P. Doyle Library at Santa Rosa Junior College \\(SRJ
 C\\) proudly presents “JERROLD BALLAINE: LAND AND SEA\,” paintings by 
 longtime Sebastopol resident Jerrold “Jerry” Ballaine. The exhibition 
 will be on display from March 23\, 2026\, through December 11\, 2026\, on 
 the 2nd floor of the Frank P. Doyle Library during open hours.\n\nTo mark 
 the opening of the exhibition\, a reception will be held on Friday\, April
  17\, 2026\, from 2:00 to 4:00 PM in Doyle Library. This event offers th
 e public a unique opportunity to engage directly with Mr. Ballaine\, who h
 as enjoyed one of the most diverse and sustained careers of any artist wor
 king in Northern California. Further\, during the reception visitors are i
 nvited to visit the Doyle Collection\, on the 3rd and 4th floors of Doyle 
 Library.\n\nThe exhibit and reception are supported by the Art in the SRJ
 C Libraries Endowment.\n\nThere is a fee to park on campus: Daily permit $
 4\, one-hour metered parking $1/hour.
LOCATION:Frank P. Doyle Library
URL:https://libraries.santarosa.edu/art_srjc_libraries
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
