 :00 PM\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Categories: Bilingual\, 
 Culinary Arts\, Kids\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n8-13\n\n$200 – Registration Cost\n
 \nStudents will learn Spanish vocabulary through doing art\, learning abou
 t Mexican culture\, and cooking over 4 weeks.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nLearn
  basic Spanish greetings\, family\, animal\, and food vocabulary.\n\nExplo
 re Mexican culture through Lotería\, Día de los Muertos\, alebrijes\, pa
 pel picado\, and piñatas while creating related crafts.\n\nParticipate in
  games and activities that reinforce Spanish words and cultural traditions
 .\n\nLearn essential knife skills.\n\nLearn to cook the following deliciou
 s dishes: Seared black pepper ahi tuna with pico de gallo\, guacamole\, m
 ango habanero passion fruit salsa\, served in a tortilla chip. Cesar Salad
  with homemade croutons and dressing. Sopes with shredded beef and chicken
 .\n\nOn the final day\, students and their families will celebrate Día de
