BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma County Philharmonic in concert - FANNY\, FLORENCE & SAM
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T213000
UID:260331aGvelPczIESgT047BTxCdg
DESCRIPTION:Norman Gamboa\, conductor\n\nEsther Rayo\, soprano\n\nSAMUEL C
 OLERIDGE-TAYLOR Idyll\, Op.44 \n\nFANNY MENDELSSOHN Hero und Leander\n\nF
 LORENCE PRICE Symphony No. 1  \n\nJoin us for a program featuring three 
 under- appreciated composers whose works are finally receiving the attenti
 on they deserve.\n\n ♪ Samuel Coleridge-Taylor’s lovely Idyll sets 
 a reflective and poetic tone with its tender melodies and pastoral eleganc
 e.\n\n♪ Fanny Mendelssohn’s dramatic cantata\, Hero und Leander\, we
 aves a tragic Greek myth into music of passion and vivid orchestration.\n\
 n♪ Florence Price’s groundbreaking Symphony No. 1 blends classical 
 forms with African American spirituals and folk rhythms creating an iconic
  20th century American masterpiece. \n\n​Come celebrate the breadth of 
 orchestral music and its enduring power to surprise\, delight\, and move t
 he human spirit!
LOCATION:Jackson Theatre (Sonoma Country Day School)
URL:https://www.socophil.org/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
