DESCRIPTION:ART HATCHERY OPEN STUDIO\n\nSaturday\, April 18 \, 2026\n\n12 
 pm – 5 pm\n\nArt Hatchery Studios\n\n401 7th street   \\( between F & 
 G streets\\)\n\nPetaluma\, Ca 94952\n\nThe Art Hatchery is a diverse group
  of Petaluma artists working across painting\, photography\, fiber art\, p
 rintmaking\, and mixed media. This is not a gallery—it’s a living\, wo
 rking studio environment where creativity happens every day. During Open S
 tudios\, visitors can step inside\, meet the artists\, and discover origin
 al work in an authentic\, approachable setting.\n\nThe Art Hatchery\, a hi
 storic brick chicken hatchery built in 1906\, has been converted into arti
 st studios.  Artists in this collective include:\n\n Lance Kuehne: fine 
 art photographer / https://lancekuehne.com/\n\n See See Lo: painter / htt
 ps://www.botzilla.com/seeseelo.html\n\n Nancy Lloyd: oil painter / https:
