BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Park Rx—Intermediate Hiking for Fitness
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T130000
UID:260227kMqaX1KauE6YgmmTIyFxJw
DESCRIPTION:If you have previously completed the Beginner Hiking f
 or Fitness Program\, or can hike a little more than 4 miles wi
 th at least 1\,000 ft of elevation\, this hiking series is for
  you! The program leaders will guide you on 8 weekly hikes wit
 h the challenge increasing each week. Leaders will have group di
 scussions about gear\, hydration\, hiking poles\, first aid and p
 acing\, etc. The group's final hike aims for Bald Mountain\, whe
 re hikers can enjoy stunning vistas.\n\nThe following is a list 
 of possible routes specifically selected for this hiking series: 
 \n\n1) Sat 3/7 — Creekside + Waterfall loop\, 3.6 miles\, 750
  ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 2) Sat 3/14 – Vista Tra
 il loop\, 3.4 miles\, 830 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 3
 ) Sat 3/21 – Goodspeed to Nattkemper bench\, 3.8 miles\, 1\,24
 0 ft elevation \\[meet @ Goodspeed lot\\] 4) Sat 3/28 – Hillsi
 de to Neptune table + Meadow\, 4.4 miles\, 970 ft elevation \\[
 meet @ White Barn\\] 5) Sat 4/4 – Hillside + Vista Trail loop
 \, 3.6 miles\, 1\,070 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 6) Sa
 t 4/11 – False Lake Meadow & Lake Ilsanjo loop in Trionne-Ann
 adel SP\, 6.1 miles\, 670 ft elevation \\[meet @ Annadel's Cobbl
 estone Trailhead\\] 7) Sat 4/18 – Fern Lake + Orchard loop in
  SDC/Jack London SHP\, 5.5 miles\, 1\,460 ft elevation \\[meet @
  Walnut & North St inside SDC\; park on Grove St\\] 8) Sat 4/2
 5 – Bald Mtn summit (w/optional Headwaters detour\, 5.8 miles)\
 , 5.1 miles\, 1\,670 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\]\n\nPlea
 se note these routes are subject to change based on the group 
 and weather. Wear appropriate footwear for rocky or slippery trai
 ls\, and layers. Bring water\, and if desired\, a snack. The gr
 oup will be limited to 35 participants. \n\nThe hiking series co
 sts $80 (plus a $10 parking fee per visit. Note that the Sugar
 loaf Annual Pass is $59 and valid at Sugarloaf and Jack London
  SHP)\, or free-of-cost for participants with a January 2025 or
  newer Park Rx from a Sonoma County Medical Provider.  The num
 ber of available Park Rx tickets is limited\; please have your 
 Rx ready at the time of sign up.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/inthffspring26
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Painting Produce - 2 Day Watercolor Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T160000
UID:260225HezTNwDhZUOnAiKurIp-ew
DESCRIPTION:In this 2 week introductory course\, participants will learn a
  unique approach to watercolor\, intended to alleviate the frustration tha
 t many experience when learning this beautiful yet challenging medium. \n
 \nThe class will practice basic drawing in addition to watercolor techniqu
 e\, with a focus on strengthening one’s observational skills while learn
 ing a step by step layering process that trains the artist to see value an
 d color.\n\nOur unifying subject will be seasonal produce - fruits\, veggi
 es and herbs\, that we will render from life. These subjects are great for
  beginners and experienced watercolor painters alike\; their organic shape
 s make them forgiving drawing subjects\, but their beauty can be a muse fo
 r life.\n\nAll experience levels welcome and all materials provided.\n\nLo
 cation: 755 Petaluma Ave\, Sebastopol\, CA\n\nDates: 2 Saturdays - April 1
 1th\, 18th\n\nTime: 1 - 4 pm\n\nRegistration Fee: $135\n\nAges: Adults\n\n
 Skill Level: All Levels
LOCATION:Art & Soul of Sebastopol
URL:https://www.hannahdrawstrees.com/painting-produce-register-april
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Joose
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T000000
UID:260224e0B-tMrk7UyJ7YHglpkvxg
DESCRIPTION:JOOSE is a high-energy ‘90s rock tribute band dedicated to r
 esurrecting the golden era of alternative and grunge. From the brooding de
 pths of Seattle grunge to the pop-rock chart-toppers of the decade\, our s
 etlist is a time capsule of songs that defined a generation.\n\nFormed by 
 a group of seasoned musicians with a passion for all things ‘90s\, JOOSE
  channels the raw emotion and dynamic energy of bands like Nirvana\, Pearl
  Jam\, Smashing Pumpkins\, Green Day\, Foo Fighters\, and more. Each perfo
 rmance is a nostalgic journey back to a time when flannel ruled\, MTV play
 ed music videos\, and rock music spoke to the heart of the culture.\n\nWit
 h authentic instrumentation\, dynamic vocals\, and a stage presence that c
 aptures the spirit of the era\, JOOSE is more than a tribute – it’s a 
 full-on revival. Whether you're rocking out to grunge classics or swaying 
 to iconic ballads\, we’ll transport you back to the days of Discman play
 ers and cassette mixtapes.\n\nGet ready to relive the angst\, the anthems\
 , and the attitude. JOOSE is your backstage pass to the ‘90s rock experi
 ence you’ll never forget!
LOCATION:Vintage Space
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107788651?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Breathing Room: Writing for Stillness and Peace
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T120000
UID:260218d__edtxFXEicEWOoVhkYXg
DESCRIPTION:Online Mini-Retreat with James Crews Breathing Room: Writing f
 or Stillness and Peace\n\nSaturday\, April 18\, 10-12 PT \\(1-3 pm ET\\)\n
 \nJoin poet and editor James Crews for a supportive and encouraging retrea
 t focusing on rest and peace through writing. We will work from poems and 
 prompts from his latest book\, Breathing Room \\(available March 17\\)\, a
 nd create together in a stress-free and tender space. \n\nThere will be t
 ime for sharing what you write\, if you wish\, but there is no pressure to
  do so\, and this workshop is ideal for writers of all levels and backgrou
 nds.\n\nJames Crews is the author of Turning Toward Grief: Reflections on 
 Life\, Loss & Appreciation\, Breathing Room: Poems of Rest & Retreat\, and
  editor of several bestselling poetry anthologies\, including Love Is for 
 All of Us\, a collection of LGBTQ\\+ love poems co-edited with his husband
 \, Brad Peacock. He has also edited The Wonder of Small Things \\(winner o
 f the New England Book Award\\)\, The Path to Kindness \\(winner of the Na
 utilus Award\\)\, and How to Love the World\, which has sold over 100\,000
  copies to date. He has been featured on NPR’s Morning Edition\, and in 
 People Magazine\, The Boston Globe\, The New York Times Magazine\, The Sun
  Magazine\, and The Washington Post. James lives with his husband on forty
  rocky acres in Vermont that they are restoring to a habitat for pollinato
 rs and native species. jamescrews.net\n\nRegister at http://stcolumbasinve
 rness.org/breathing-room
LOCATION:St. Columba's Inverness
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/breathing-room-writing-
 for-stillness-and-peace/18150260/2026-04-18T10
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Patterns + Printing for Kids
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T120000
UID:260214ojUP6Y-_-0yBv9OaJoCP4g
DESCRIPTION:From Stamp to Table: Picnic Pattern Workshop\n\nStep into the 
 world of design and pattern-making! In this hands-on workshop\, kids will 
 explore the art of repeating patterns — just like real textile designers
 . Using hand-carved stamps\, rollers\, and stencils\, each participant wil
 l create their own bold\, colorful designs and print them on cotton tablec
 loths or picnic napkin sets to take home.\n\nWe’ll talk about color\, ba
 lance\, and rhythm in design — then bring those ideas to life on fabric.
  The result? A totally functional\, one-of-a-kind textile piece perfect fo
 r family picnics\, kitchen tables\, or gifting.
LOCATION:Art Escape
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/patterns-printing-for-k
 ids/18120576/2026-04-18T10
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Butter & Egg Days Parade & Festival 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T170000
UID:260212OMOwI-NLD06yfJ-7YuWmmw
DESCRIPTION:Theme: "America's Birthday - Petaluma Style"\n\n*Celebrating 
 250 years of independence\, ingenuity\, and small-town pride.*\n\n“Ameri
 cas’ Birthday – Petaluma Style” celebrates the nation’s 250th Birt
 hday by honoring Petaluma’s deep agricultural roots and hometown spirit.
  This year’s Butter & Egg Days Parade recognizes the farmers\, families\
 , immigrants\, makers\, entrepreneurs\, and creatives whose hard work\, im
 agination\, and ingenuity reflect the enduring American Dream. This celebr
 ation also pays respect to the Indigenous peoples who first stewarded this
  land\, the courage of our founders\, and the dedication of the dairy and 
 egg farming community that shaped our town. Rooted in community\, innovati
 on\, and independence\, the parade celebrates the small-town spirit that c
 ontinues to make Petaluma a vibrant place to call home. Head to Downtown P
 etaluma and celebrate with our community on this day of fun\, history\, an
 d local pride!\n\nParade participants incorporate the theme *“America's
  Birthday - Petaluma Style”* into their entry design. The theme gives n
 onprofits\, businesses\, organizations\, and individuals lots of options f
 or showing off their creativity in their designs. All parade entries will 
 be judged on how well their entry portrays this year's theme - winners ann
 ounced on the website! Check back later to see which entries take home the
  prizes and earn bragging rights.\n\nThe Butter & Egg Days festivities kic
 k off on Saturday\, **April 11** with the **Opening Ceremonies** at the
  Petaluma Historical Library and Museum (20 Fourth St)\, from Noon to 1pm.
  Mayor Kevin McDonnell will read a proclamation honoring the Grand Marshal
  and Good Egg. Come enjoy this display that shows the heart of our communi
 ty.\n\nOne week later on Saturday\, **April 18\,** the Butter & Egg Days
  **Parade** steps off at noon and marches through the historic downtown. 
 The parade showcases over 100 units with approximately 3\,000 participants
  and 200 volunteers. Clover Sonoma returns to lead the Clover **Kids’ P
 arade**\, which precedes the main parade at 11:30am with a procession of p
 reschoolers and primary grade youngsters and their families.\n\nThe parade
  is surrounded by a **Festival** that spreads over four city blocks from 
 10am-5pm offering a wide variety of food\, crafts\, beverage gardens\, two
  large kid areas\, live music\, and more! This annual event aims to bring 
 together the community for a day of fun and entertainment.\n\nThe followin
 g weekend\, Downtown Petaluma continues the celebration with the Annual Sp
 ring Antique Faire\, on Sunday\, **April 26**.\n\nHappy Butter & Egg Days
 !!!\n\nVisit ButterAndEggDays.com for more information!
LOCATION:Historic Downtown Petaluma
URL:http://www.ButterAndEggDays.com 
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
