SUMMARY:Park Rx—Yoga Hikes 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T123000
UID:260124sc3YO1dF40yOU-AKsoIUHQ
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy your yoga experience in the beautiful setting of
  our park! Susan Topf’s Yoga Hike balances a mix of easy hik
 ing and gentle yoga postures\, breath work and guided meditation\
 , no mat necessary. The route varies on weather conditions and 
 group interest\, typically covering 2-3 miles of varied terrain. 
 All levels and ages welcome.\n\nTickets are $20.  Please wear wea
 ther appropriate clothing to feel comfortable being in a natural 
 setting and bring water (as needed). Meet outside the Visitor Ce
 nter unless otherwise noted in the reminder email prior to the 
 hike. Free with a November 2025 or newer Park Rx from a participating Sono
 ma County Medical Provider Limited to 12 participants.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/2026yoga-hikes
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Laguna Stewards at Colgan Creek/ Día de Laguna Stewards
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T120000
UID:251206ysbuuGmKXEOZfmjBufaDdQ
DESCRIPTION:Come be a part of something special at Colgan Creek with the L
 aguna de Santa Rosa Foundation! Join us for a fun and rewarding day of han
 ds-on stewardship as we care for this creek. Starting at Taylor Mountain a
 nd flowing through Santa Rosa to Roseland and then to the Laguna de Santa 
 Rosa\, Colgan Creek has gone through many stages of restoration\, and we w
 ould like you to be a part of this new phase!\n\nThis is your chance to se
 e the creek's incredible transformation and make a real impact in its ongo
 ing care. Whether you're new to ecological restoration or an experienced v
 olunteer\, everyone is welcome—of all ages and abilities. Let's come tog
 ether to nurture this beautiful creek and continue its journey toward rest
 oration. We can't wait to share this experience with you!\n\nIMPORTANT: Lo
 cation details will be sent via email upon registration.\n\nPLEASE NOTE: A
 ll ages are welcome! No experience is necessary\; tools and training are p
 rovided.\n\nA big thank you to our Phase 3 project funders\, which include
  the Department of Water Resources Urban Streams Restoration Program\, the
  Wildlife Conservation Board\, and the Sonoma County Agricultural Preserva
 tion and Open Space District. Additional Phase 3 partners include the City
  of Santa Rosa and Rainforest Rising. We could not do this work without th
 em.\n\n¡Ven a formar parte de algo especial en el arroyo Colgan con la La
 guna de Santa Rosa Foundation! Únete a nosotros para disfrutar de un día
  divertido y gratificante de restauración mientras cuidamos de este arroy
 o. El arroyo Colgan\, que comienza en Taylor Mountain y fluye a través de
  Santa Rosa hasta Roseland y luego hasta la Laguna de Santa Rosa\, ha pasa
 do por muchas etapas de restauración\, ¡y nos gustaría que fueras parte
  de esta nueva etapa!\n\nEsta es tu oportunidad de ver la increíble trans
 formación del arroyo y generar un impacto real en su cuidado continuo. Ya
  seas nuevo en la restauración ecológica o un voluntario experimentado\,
  todos son bienvenidos\, de todas las edades y habilidades. Unámonos para
  cuidar este hermoso arroyo y continuar su viaje hacia la restauración. 
 ¡Estamos ansiosos por compartir esta experiencia contigo!\n\nLos detalles
  de la ubicación se enviarán por correo electrónico al registrarse.\n\n
 NOTA: ¡Son bienvenidas personas de todas las edades! No se necesita exper
 iencia\; se proporcionan herramientas y capacitación.\n\nAgradecemos enor
 memente a los financiadores de la Fase 3 del proyecto\, entre ellos el Pro
 grama de Restauración de Arroyos Urbanos del Departamento de Recursos Hí
 dricos\, la Junta de Conservación de la Vida Silvestre y el Distrito de P
 reservación Agrícola y Espacios Abiertos del Condado de Sonoma. Otros so
 cios de la Fase 3 incluyen la Ciudad de Santa Rosa y Rainforest Rising. ¡
 Sin ellos\, no podríamos realizar este trabajo!
LOCATION:Colgan Creek
URL:https://colgancreekphase3vol3.eventbrite.com  
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Annadel Half Marathon\, 10K\, & 5K
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T150000
UID:2510217dO3uomJ0k6jkkc6Ndw7Xw
DESCRIPTION:The Annadel Half Marathon is a non-profit fundraising event. O
 ver the past 16 years\, we have raised funds to make the park a more beaut
 iful place for all to enjoy!   The Half Marathon course is a hilly\, and
  technical course designed for the experienced trail runner looking for a 
 challenge. Enjoy gorgeous scenery with green meadows\, wild flowers\, and 
 variety of beautiful trees. The race starts at the Spring Lake Oak Knolls 
 picnic area and winds through Spring Lake Park before climbing into Annade
 l State Park. The Annadel Half Marathon is a tough course with over 1\,500
  feet of elevation gain over rocky and rooted terrain. The 5k course is an
  out and back route heading up a gravel fire road slightly into Annadel St
 ate park.
LOCATION:Spring Lake Regional Park
URL:https://www.annadelhalfmarathon.com/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
