BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Saturday Live Music at Spicy Vines feat. Jenerator
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T180000
UID:260206WESCfsSy6E-MlWlCIIrM3Q
DESCRIPTION:Where unforgettable wines\, live music\, and good vibes come t
 ogether.\n\nJoin us every Saturday from 3–6 PM at Spicy Vines for a tast
 ing room experience like no other — where top local musicians from acros
 s the Bay Area meet our award-winning small-lot wines. From Rock & Roll an
 d Blues to Jazz\, Bluegrass\, and Americana\, each weekend brings new soun
 ds and new reasons to raise a glass. \n\nJenerator Jenerator is a Northe
 rn California jam band duo blending rock\, funk\, blues\, and soul into po
 werful live performances full of heart\, rhythm\, and groove. \n\nDetails
 \n\nNo cover. Walk-ins are welcome\, but this event tends to fill up quick
 ly\, so we recommend making a reservation. We are dog and family friendly!
LOCATION:Spicy Vines Winery
URL:https://spicyvines.com/event/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Petaluma River High Tide Upstream Paddle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T144500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T164500
UID:260129gJ-6_SIftkuUwQEyHcEnyg
DESCRIPTION:When the tide is high\, the Petaluma River opens into a quiete
 r\, greener world.\n\nJoin The Floathouse crew for a gentle\, guided paddl
 e upstream\, timed to higher tides that allow access beyond the downtown c
 hannel and into a tranquil tidal slough. With extra water beneath us\, we
 ’re able to glide into calm\, lush stretches of the river that are norma
 lly out of reach.\n\nThis unhurried paddle highlights the natural beauty o
 f the Petaluma River’s brackish\, tidal waterway. Watch for great egrets
 \, blue herons\, snowy egrets\, turtles basking along the banks\, and abun
 dant plant life. The calm water and peaceful surroundings create a deeply 
 grounding experience—many guests say they feel their stress melt away wi
 thin minutes.\n\nAlong the way\, knowledgeable guides share stories of the
  river’s ecology and human history\, offering insight into how this uppe
 r channel has shaped—and continues to shape—Petaluma. It’s a rare op
 portunity to experience how close wild nature lives to the heart of downto
 wn.\n\nBeginner-friendly. Sit-on-top kayaks and all gear provided.
LOCATION:The Floathouse Petaluma
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/petaluma-river-high-tid
 e-upstream-paddle/17972590/2026-04-18T14
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
