BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Callie Watts
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T000000
UID:260312fiyvgWIKg0K8JaVrucKyQw
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:The California
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107935520?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lauren Jenkins
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T000000
UID:260312Uap6Q0vIUUuf3iOf-iypOQ
DESCRIPTION:Americana singer-songwriter Lauren Jenkins has been a touring 
 artist since she was 15 years old. The Texas born\, Carolina-raised artist
  chose a life that would fit perfectly in the songs she writes: across cou
 ntless smoky bars\, fake IDs\, and endless miles on the road\, music has b
 een her one constant companion. Named an Artist to Watch by the New York T
 imes\, Billboard\, Rolling Stone\, Pandora\, and many more\, she was also 
 chosen as a member of the “Class of 2019” by influential radio DJ Bobb
 y Bones\, and made her TODAY Show debut as Elvis Duran’s Artist of the M
 onth. An accomplished actress and filmmaker\, Lauren wrote\, produced\, an
 d starred in an original short film titled 'Running Out of Road' that acco
 mpanied the release of her critically-acclaimed debut album\, NO SAINT\,  
 on Big Machine Records. Her short film"Running Out Of Road" was an officia
 l selection at Roswell Film Festival and screened during the Nashville Fil
 m Festival\, SXSW\, and Sundance. \n\nShe has hosted as a Guest DJ on Siri
 us XM's E Street channel. Her love of Bruce Springsteen compelled her to r
 ecord two of the Bosses songs "Stolen Car" and "Hungry Heart"\, which also
  debuted on the E Street Channel. \n\nLauren has built a loyal following i
 n Europe and the UK after her debut at C2C festival in March of 2019. Just
  before the world shut down in 2020 Lauren was just coming home from a suc
 cessiful tour in Europe and the UK. \n\nSince the pandemic\, Lauren has be
 en connecting with audiences through virtual "living room concerts" until 
 she can get back on the road. \n\nIn May of 2020\, she released “Ain’t
  That Hard\,” her first song as a fully independent artist. Part 1 of he
 r sophomore record "Miles On Me" is out now.\n\n"“Lauren is unapologetic
 ally raw at times\, uncompromising and unflinching in the way she looks at
  the world and herself. If you are looking for someone with meaning\, some
 one with a knack for melody and someone with an honest\, authentic view of
  life\, love and relationships\, then Lauren Jenkins always has been\, and
  even more now\, is the perfect artist for you.” - Lyric Magazine
LOCATION:Brasswood Cellars
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107917926?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:GLYPH  - Art Exhibition
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T150000
UID:2603100YO7mrcnIku3Hp5YakE9WA
DESCRIPTION:Glyph will be on view through May 3. Personal Space is open Su
 ndays 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. and by appointment.\n\nBig news! Personal Space is
  back from our \\(much needed\\) hiatus. Join us next Sunday\, March 15 \
 \(2-5pm\\) for the opening of  Glyph. This is our first opening since Vil
 lage opened up next door\, and it’s sure to be a party!\n\nFeaturing thi
 rteen artists from the Bay Area and beyond\, Glyph embraces a liminal spac
 e which allows subconscious connections to reign and centers gut feeling a
 s a source of poetry\, mystery\, and magic. Collectively\, these artists d
 raw from an enigmatic lexicon of symbols\, favoring inscrutable familiarit
 y over anything known or quantified. This intuitive language manifests thr
 ough a varied approach to material translation that underscores\, and cele
 brates\, our innate ability to understand things deeply without having to 
 define them in words.\n\nGlyph features works by:\n\nSadie Buckner \n\nLu
 is Estrada \n\nRochele Gomez \n\nKainoa Gruspe \n\nLéonie Guyer \n\nK
 lea McKenna\n\nMitzi Pederson \n\nBen Peterson \n\nJ Pendleton\n\nRobert
  Smithson \n\nEmma Spertus \n\nHenna Vainio \n\nRichard Zimmerman \n\n
 See link for details and artist bios.
LOCATION:Personal Space
URL:https://personalspace.space/exhibitions/glyph
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
