DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T170000
UID:260309gBcHfk85sUaMt3Wbj6nt3Q
DESCRIPTION:Concert III\n\nLondon Symphony\n\nSunday\, April 19\, 2026 at 
 3PM\n\nEmpress Theatre\n\nProkofiev\, Classical Symphony\n\nSaint-Saëns\,
  Cello Concerto No. 1\n\n     Isaac Pastor-Chemak\, cello soloist\n\n
 Haydn Symphony No.104 London\n\nMarc Taddei\, conducting\n\nOur grand fina
 le brings Haydn’s last and greatest symphony to the stage—his jubilant
  farewell to the form he helped define. The evening opens with Prokofiev
 ’s cheeky Classical Symphony and Saint-Saëns’ passionate Cello Concer
 to No. 1\, performed by our exceptional principal cellist Isaac Pastor-Che
 rnik. His playing combines fire\, grace\, and total command of the instrum
 ent.
LOCATION:Empress Theatre
URL:https://vallejosymphony.org/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Painting Workshop with Maria De Los Angeles
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T160000
UID:260216XbY_OHVR2EeF9XzCHYXkEA
DESCRIPTION:Join renowned artist Maria de Los Angeles for a nature-inspire
 d full-day painting workshop that explores gestural watercolor techniques 
 combined with fine line details in gouache. Participants will create dynam
 ic\, all-over compositions reflecting the ecological beauty of Jack London
  State Historic Park. All skill levels are welcome to be part of this arti
 stic experience. Recommended for ages 12 and older.\n\nAbout the Artist\n\
 nMaria De Los Angeles is a Mexican-born\, American artist who addresses id
 eas of migration\, belonging\, and identity through her drawing\, painting
 \, printmaking\, and wearable sculptures. She holds an MFA from Yale Schoo
 l of Art \\(2015\\)\, a BFA from Pratt Institute \\(2013\\)\, and an Assoc
 iate Degree from Santa Rosa Junior College \\(2010\\).\n\nMaria was awarde
 d the Blair Dickinson Memorial Prize by the Yale School of Art in 2015 and
  the William Aguilar Cultural Award in 2023\, by the AHHE American Associa
 tion of Hispanics in Higher Education Inc. for her artwork and her role wi
 thin her communities.\n\nShe has been an Artist in Residence at the Sun Va
 lley Museum of Art\, Anderson Ranch Arts Center\, MASS MOCA\, El Museo del
  Barrio\, LACMA\, and Monira Foundation\, among others. She has had solo e
 xhibitions at Schneider Museum of Art \\(2018 & 2019\\)\, the Museum of So
 noma County \\(2019\\)\, and Goggleworks \\(2022\\). She is currently a Cr
 itic and Assistant Director of Graduate Studies for the Painting/Printmaki
 ng Program at the Yale School of Art.\n\nMost recently her work was on vie
 w at the Sun Valley Museum of Art and is currently on view at the Fairfiel
 d University Art Museum.\n\nDe Los Angeles is based in Jersey City\, NJ\, 
 Santa Rosa\, CA\, and New Haven\, CT. Her work has been featured in Hypera
 llergic\, Artnet\, New York Magazine\, HelloGiggles\, and The Observer. IG
  @delosangelesart https://www.mariadelosangelesart.com/
LOCATION:Jack London State Historic Park
URL:https://jacklondonpark.com/events/painting-workshop-with-maria-de-los-
 angeles-2026/ 
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wood Engraving - 2 Day Intensive Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T150000
UID:260216PzGUtV52hUan2o4EqZPqAw
DESCRIPTION:This two-day workshop introduces the art and practice of wood 
 engraving. The hard woods used to make wood engraving blocks are type-high
  (.918”\, the height of metal type) and are cut across the grain rather 
 than parallel to it like wood cuts. These durable end-grain blocks allow f
 or extensive detail. The tools used are gravers (or burins) that are diffe
 rent than the gouge tools used for wood cuts. This versatile form of print
 making requires little space and minimal equipment and is perfect for a sm
 all home studio.\n\nDay 1: We will start with a brief history of wood engr
 aving including its long relationship to letterpress printing\, and we wil
 l study examples of period and contemporary wood engravings. Students will
  begin with a sampler block to explore the effects of various tools\, pro
 of the block on the press\, and transfer a design onto another block to c
 onsider the approach for their first engraving.\n\nDay 2: Students will l
 earn how to sharpen their gravers and continue to engrave their blocks. We
  will become familiar with basic use of the Vandercook SP-15 cylinder pres
 s to ink and proof the block and troubleshoot issues when printing. Printi
 ng an edition of a block will be discussed\, and those wanting to contribu
 te a print to the workshop portfolio are encouraged to do so. Students wil
 l leave the workshop with the skills to master the graver tool to create i
 ntricate prints\, a value test block for future reference\, an instructive
  handout\, a block to edition\, and a portfolio of workshop prints.\n\nLev
 el: Beginner – no previous experience necessary\n\n*Includes $50 materia
 ls fee\, which covers #3 elliptical tint tool and two 3”x 4” end-grain
  maple blocks)*\n\n**INSTRUCTOR**\n\n**Colleen Dwire** initially learned w
 ood engraving in a workshop with American Master John DePol and has been p
 racticing for over thirty years. She exhibits her prints internationally. 
 Colleen is an elected member of the Society of Wood Engravers (UK) and ser
 ves as Secretary and Exhibitions Officer for Wood Engravers’ Network (US
 A) and as a board member of North Bay Letterpress Arts. Learn more at www.
 colleendwire.com and follow on colleendwire.bsky.social.
LOCATION:North Bay Letterpress Arts
URL:https://www.northbayletterpressarts.org/for-sale/2026-wood-engraving
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Taste Of Pine Mountain
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T153000
UID:260206JqxP3QfXrkGwm_jT5ksrhQ
DESCRIPTION:An intimate\, mountaintop experience designed for those who lo
 ve great wine\, beautiful landscapes\, and moments that feel truly special
 .\n\nJoin us on Sunday\, April 19\, 2025\, for a day that takes you high
  above Alexander Valley to explore Pine Mountain through the lens of wine\
 , place\, and people. This curated experience brings together sweeping vie
 ws\, unreleased barrel tastings\, and relaxed\, thoughtful hospitality —
  all led by winemaker Doug Hackett himself.\n\nYou’ll begin with a wel
 come wine and bites as you take in the breathtaking scenery\, followed by 
 an intimate barrel tasting of unreleased wines from Spicy Vines and Pine 
 Mountain Vineyards. Afterward\, we’ll settle in for a laid-back BBQ lun
 ch\, generous pours\, and easy conversation — the kind that only happens
  when you slow down and savor where you are.\n\nThis isn’t just another 
 tasting. It’s a rare opportunity to experience Pine Mountain in a way fe
 w ever do.
LOCATION:Spicy Vines Winery
URL:https://spicyvines.com/event/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
