BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Brandlin Estate Wine & Food Tasting Experience
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T160000
UID:2603128mNaWEe-VkGSrBzkYg-evg
DESCRIPTION:Born on the rugged slopes of Mount Veeder\, Brandlin Estate pr
 oduces wines of structure\, intensity\, and place. The Brandlin Experience
  offers an in-depth exploration of this historic vineyard site through a c
 urated tasting of five estate-grown wines—including Zinfandel from centu
 ry-old vines and the estate’s signature Cabernet Sauvignon. This seated\
 , guided experience invites guests to delve into the mountain terroir thro
 ugh the lens of small-lot winemaking. Each wine reflects the elevation\, e
 xposure\, and rocky soils that define the Brandlin Estate. For an added di
 mension\, guests may opt to include seasonal bites\, thoughtfully paired t
 o complement the structure and complexity of the wines. This experience is
  hosted at the picturesque Boathouse.
LOCATION:Brandlin Estate 
URL:https://www.exploretock.com/brandlinestate/experience/565565/the-brand
 lin-wine-food-tasting-experience?date=2026-03-12&size=2&time=10%3A00
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Overeaters Anonymous (OA) Newcomer Meeting in Santa Rosa
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T170000
UID:260212MtPHVeqQpkyUrs7htQFGqw
DESCRIPTION:**Is Food a Problem for You? You Are Not Alone.**\n\nOvereater
 s Anonymous (OA) is a fellowship of people who support each other in recov
 ering from compulsive eating and food behaviors. If you feel you have a pr
 oblem with food\, OA welcomes you—no matter what your background\, belie
 fs\, or eating habits.\n\nWe hold an in-person newcomer meeting on **Sunda
 ys from 4:00 – 5:00 PM** **at Christ Church United Methodist\, 1717 Yulu
 pa Ave.\, Room #4\, Santa Rosa**. Contact: Abigail (707) 293-5888. You may
  view all North Bay OA in-person and online meetings at https://www.northb
 ayoa.org/meetings.html .\n\nIn OA\, members experience **spiritual\, emoti
 onal\, and physical recovery** by practicing the **Twelve Steps** and livi
 ng by their spiritual principles—one day at a time.\n\nOA is **not** a d
 iet club or calorie-counting program.\n\nMembers have different plans of e
 ating.\n\nOA does **not** endorse any specific food plan.\n\nIf food is ca
 using problems in your life\, you don’t have to struggle alone. Recovery
  is possible\, and help is available.\n\n**Visit:** https://www.northbayoa
 .org/\n\n**Find a meeting:** https://www.northbayoa.org/meetings.html
LOCATION:Christ Church United Methodist
URL:https://www.northbayoa.org/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
