BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Benefit for Walker Creek Music Camp - An Evening of American Roots
  Music
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T210000
UID:260331yx9XeI9bgUignaJBgoAaGw
DESCRIPTION:Walker Creek Music Camp Presents Teacher Concert Series IV Ben
 efit Concert Celebrating American Roots Music\n\nThe concert supports Walk
 er Creek Music Camp’s mission to provide world-class music education and
  expand access to traditional roots music through classes\, youth programs
 \, and scholarships.\n\nThe evening will feature these outstanding faculty
  and alumni performing bluegrass\, old-time\, jazz\, and swing:\n\nWalker 
 Creek All-Stars A “supergroup” of current and former instructors featu
 ring: Yoseff Tucker \\(guitar\\)\, Tod Livingston \\(dobro\\)\, Bethany Ra
 ine Sorkey \\(bass\\)\, Paul Shelasky \\(fiddle\\)\, Ryan Breen \\(banjo\\
 )\, and Tom Bekeny \\(mandolin\\).\n\nHildaland A duo blending Scottish an
 d American traditions featuring fiddler Louise Bichan and mandolin virtuos
 o Ethan Setiawan.\n\nPacific Drive A high-energy bluegrass band formed at 
 Walker Creek Music Camp featuring Dana Frankel\, David Thiessen\, Jesse Fi
 chman\, Helen Foley\, and Sam Reed.\n\nAbout Walker Creek Music Camp Found
 ed in 2013\, Walker Creek Music Camp is a California nonprofit dedicated t
 o teaching\, preserving\, and celebrating American roots music. The camp o
 ffers world-class instruction for students of all ages and hosts sessions 
 twice each year at Walker Creek Ranch Conference Center.\n\nThe camp’s M
 usic & More \\(M&M’s\\) youth program provides tuition-free instruction 
 for children ages 6–13\, along with scholarships and work-trade opportun
 ities that help make music education accessible to all.\n\nMore informatio
 n: walkercreekmusiccamp.org
LOCATION:Sebastopol Community Cultural Center
URL:https://www.walkercreekmusiccamp.org
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
