BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Especies de Sonoma: Aves (Sonoma Species: Birds) en Español
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T140000
UID:260405ziOn2SzRq0a73dO5ajeNMg
DESCRIPTION:A "Rutas y Aventuras" program by Jack London Park Partners and
  " Senderos Naturales" by the Sonoma Ecology Center.\n\nOn this hike\, gui
 ded in Spanish\, learn how to use the Merlin Bird ID app at Jack London St
 ate Historic Park. In the spring\, this park comes alive with a multitude 
 of bird species arriving to build their nests and forage for food—rangin
 g from swallows and hummingbirds to hawks and owls. Come discover the wond
 erful birds found in the Sonoma Valley!\n\nThis workshop will focus on:\n\
 n• How to use Merlin Bird ID to identify birds by song and photograph\n\
 n• Basic tips for observing nature and improving your identification ski
 lls\n\n• General information about common birds\, plants\, and animals f
 ound within the Sonoma Valley and Sonoma County\n\n• How these apps help
  scientists and parks protect local biodiversity\n\nThis program is ideal 
 for beginners\, families\, nature lovers\, and anyone with a curious mind.
  No prior experience is required. We will proceed step-by-step\, and there
  will be ample time for questions and guided practice.  This is an easy h
 ike with a moderate incline.\n\nRegistration and more information is avail
 able at https://jacklondonpark.com/events/aves/.\n\nJoin us again on April
  25 to use your new skills to identify plants and animals at Sugarloaf Rid
 ge State Park with the help of iNaturalist. Register at https://sec.regfox
 .com/senderos26-cnc \\($5 deposit applies for adults\\).
LOCATION:Jack London State Historic Park
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/especies-de-sonoma-aves
 -sonoma-species-birds-en-espa-ol/18510158/2026-04-24T09
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
