 hat occupy your ears long after they're over. \n\nOn occasion\, a dBRx or
 iginal sneaks its way in.
LOCATION:Wonderstump!  Art Collective
URL:https://www.tickettailor.com/events/wonderstump/2144944
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Emergence - Spring Through the Eyes of the Artists
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T160000
UID:260401nl6qL5ib3UW9W-KWYmoxNw
DESCRIPTION:"Emergence" brings together the Artists of Fulton Crossing to 
 explore what Spring means to their creative lives. Spring is more than a s
 eason. It's a metaphor. It's renewal\, risk\, color\, thawing\, blooming\,
  awakening\, and sometimes even struggles. The public is invited to enjoy 
 this free Art exhibit and to take time to wander through the artists studi
 os and gallery spaces. Meet the artists at our opening reception March 21s
 t. Upcoming Art Workshops: March 21: Painting Easter Cookies. April 18: Ci
 gar Box Collage. May 16: Succulent Garden Centerpiece. Make treasures to b
 ring home. All ages welcome. Materials provided. E-mail Brenda at nanaspre
 ttypaper@outlook.com for preregistration and workshop info.
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/emergence-spring-through-the-eyes-of-
 the-artists/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spanish and Cooking Class for Homeschoolers
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T130000
UID:260401MmjzEjEuhUq3oPS3ovehwA
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nFridays\, April 10 – May 1\, 2026 10:00 AM – 1
 :00 PM\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Categories: Bilingual\, 
 Culinary Arts\, Kids\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n8-13\n\n$200 – Registration Cost\n
 \nStudents will learn Spanish vocabulary through doing art\, learning abou
 t Mexican culture\, and cooking over 4 weeks.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nLearn
  basic Spanish greetings\, family\, animal\, and food vocabulary.\n\nExplo
 re Mexican culture through Lotería\, Día de los Muertos\, alebrijes\, pa
 pel picado\, and piñatas while creating related crafts.\n\nParticipate in
  games and activities that reinforce Spanish words and cultural traditions
 .\n\nLearn essential knife skills.\n\nLearn to cook the following deliciou
 s dishes: Seared black pepper ahi tuna with pico de gallo\, guacamole\, m
 ango habanero passion fruit salsa\, served in a tortilla chip. Cesar Salad
  with homemade croutons and dressing. Sopes with shredded beef and chicken
 .\n\nOn the final day\, students and their families will celebrate Día de
 l Niño together. The students will cook a special meal for their parents.
  Parents will be invited so we can all eat lunch together.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/spanish-and-cooking-homesch
 ool/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
