DESCRIPTION:Learn to mix\, knead\, braid\, and bake olive oil challah. Ste
 phanie Rosenbaum Klassen will demonstrate her version of this rich\, soft 
 egg bread made with our estate-grown olive oil and local honey—perfect f
 or any celebration. We’ll also include a recipe (and taste) of Challah F
 rench Toast with Apple Cider Syrup.\n\nThe experience begins with a leisur
 ely walk through our orchard to the Apple Cottage\, where the demo takes p
 lace surrounded by the beauty of the farm. Afterward\, guests will ride ba
 ck to the Farm Shop aboard our beloved apple-themed trolley.\n\nStephanie 
 Rosenbaum Klassen is Gold Ridge Organic Farms' Farm Shop lead\, bringing y
 ears of experience as a cookbook author\, teacher\, and food writer. Her a
 cclaimed books include A Little Taste of San Francisco\, World of Doughnut
 s\, and Honey from Flower to Table. Her work has appeared in The New York 
 Times\, San Francisco Chronicle\, Edible publications\, and more.
