SUMMARY:Drawing and Composition
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T123000
UID:260326iiupsOAyG0agKEObxQ7Ckg
DESCRIPTION:Santa Rosa Junior College Lifelong Learning Offers a FREE cour
 se Drawing and Composition Course LL501\, Section Number  4235 \\(just sho
 w up and I will enroll you\\) Fridays 9:30 to 12:30 January 16 through May
  22 Roseland Campus: 950 S. Wright Road\, Santa Rosa CA 95407 Heritage Hal
 l Room 123 Amanda Rose Hopkins\,  ahopkins@santarosa.edu Class focuses on 
 Drawing with a focus on abstraction and Modernism using pencil\, ink\, oil
  pastel\, chalk pastel\, charcoal\, and collage with a focus on elements o
 f composition and design. We will explore various elements of design and c
 omposition in a nonjudgemental warm community atmosphere. A delightful mix
 ture of freedom and technique. SRJC offers noncredit courses for seniors a
 s part of its goal to provide lifelong learning. For information on joinin
 g a class please visit: https://lifelong.santarosa.edu/ No age limit for S
 RJC Lifelong Learning courses\, though they are tailored for seniors. Stud
 ents may register at any time during the semester. No fee for SRJC Lifelon
 g Learning courses. Contact Instructor for enrollment details\,  ahopkins@
 santarosa.edu The Sonoma County Junior College District does not discrimin
 ate on the basis of race\, religious creed\, color\, national origin\, anc
 estry\, ethnic group identification\, physical disability\, mental disabil
 ity\, medical condition\, genetic condition\, marital status\, sex\, gende
 r\, gender identity\, gender expression\, genetic information or sexual or
 ientation in any of its policies\, procedures or practices\; nor does the 
 District discriminate against any employees or applicants for employment o
 n the basis of their age. This non-discrimination policy covers admission\
 , access and treatment in District programs and activities--including but 
 not limited to academic admissions\, financial aid\, educational services 
 and athletics--and application for District employment. This class focuses
  on Drawing with a focus on abstraction and Modernism using pencil\, ink\,
  oil pastel\, chalk pastel\, charcoal\, and collage with a focus on elemen
 ts of composition and design. We will explore various elements of design a
 nd composition in a nonjudgemental warm community atmosphere. A delightful
  mixture of freedom and technique. Each week we will explore a different d
 rawing material and practice making various types of marks with it. We wil
 l also view drawing works by well known and obscure artists from the past 
 and present. Drawing and Composition will explore the fundamentals of comp
 osition and design in drawing and View more
LOCATION:Santa Rosa Junior College
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/drawing-and-composition/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Friday Night Comedy - Marc Yaffee - Downtown
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T220000
UID:260402FDraXFMI30myiA5YETLjvA
DESCRIPTION:Stand-up comedy in Downtown Santa Rosa\n\nVIP TABLES NOW AVAIL
 ABLE! Snag a table for 4 with preferred seating\, your own private call bu
 tton to summon service\, and your first round of drinks (or a bottle of wi
 ne) for only $95!\n\nEvery Friday night hilarious comedians from The Bay A
 rea and beyond perform at Barrel Proof Lounge. Stick around after for late
 -night karaoke! Fresh lineup of funny each Friday.\n\nThis Week: Jon Lehre
  (host) Jenny Roberts Pat McCoy\n\nHeadliner: Marc Yaffee\n\nMarc Yaffee i
 s a co-star of the historic Showtime special\, Goin’ Native\; the first-
 ever all-Native cable special. He can be seen on Amazon Prime and heard on
  SiriusXM. Marc also has two Dry Bar comedy specials\, Mid-Laugh Crisis an
 d Raising the Bar.\n\nMarc Yaffee’s diverse comedy career has landed him
  in 43 states and 11 countries spanning 4 continents. Additionally\, Marc 
 has harnessed his Native roots to comedically master the elements of natur
 e and may be the only comedian with the distinction of air\, land\, and se
 a comedic credits.\n\nHe’s entertained Alaska Airlines passengers at 30\
 ,000 feet\, performed on a flat-bed truck for U.S. Marines in Iraq (while 
 getting his head shaved)\, and performed for tens of thousands of Holland 
 America Cruise ship passengers traversing the high seas.\n\nMarc Yaffee is
  a founder and co-star of the Powwow Comedy Jam (2010 National Indian Gami
 ng Association Entertainers of the Year). Additionally\, Marc has also bee
 n seen on PBS\, FNX\, The Latino Laugh Festival\, and Comics Unleashed. He
 ’s performed six times overseas for Armed Forces Entertainment and he wo
 n the Ventura Comedy Festival’s “Funniest Person Contest” in 2012.\n
 \nFunny\, not filthy\, Marc Yaffee’s relevant & relatable sense of humor
  skewers sacred cows\, dissects societal stupidities\, and confronts commo
 n frustrations\, all with heart\, humanity\, and hilarity. Marc continues 
 to expand his comedy footprint as he tours the world performing for an eve
 r-growing\, diverse fan base. Visit **www.laughwithmarc.com**\n\n21+ Door
 s - 7p / Show - 8p $15adv / $20door\n\nCheck out **www.BarrelProofLounge.
 com** for all sorts of good times ahead.
LOCATION:Barrel Proof Lounge
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/friday-night-comedy-marc-yaffee-downtown-
 santa-rosa-tickets-1982250443437?aff=oddtdtcreator
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
