 ill your water bottle\, and grab your trekking poles for a 12-mile hike th
 rough the back country at Jack London State Historic Park.  This scenic o
 uting travels through lush spring landscapes\, where vibrant wildflowers b
 lanket the trails beneath towering evergreens. Along the way\, pause to ta
 ke in the sweeping views of Sonoma Valley and appreciate the beauty of the
  season in full bloom. This hike is considered moderate in trail steepness
  and the journey will take about six hours\, so come prepared for a full a
 nd rewarding day outdoors.
