BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Nature Hike at Lynch Canyon
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T133000
UID:260327vTm8IQNsCUKTgSQtqIJb7g
DESCRIPTION:This hike will take visitors westward along Middle Valley Trai
 l leading to Prairie Ridge. Expect about a 5 mile hike at a moderate\, but
  even pace over uneven ground. Muddy spots will have cattle prints. There 
 are steep climbs over several hills with the longest at Prairie Ridge. It
 ’s worth it to see the view of the northern San Francisco Bay.\n\nMeet i
 n the parking lot: Parking is $5. Please be prepared to pay by cash or che
 ck. Envelopes are in the iron ranger near the main gate.\n\n\\*Please note
 \, cancellation of the hike may occur due to County Fire Danger Warnings a
 nd closures of open spaces and parks. Once registered\, you will receive a
 ny updates should this ever happen. Hike level: Moderate to Moderately Str
 enuous\n\nLynch Canyon is an open space park owned by Solano Land Trust an
 d operated through partnership by Solano County Parks.
LOCATION:Lynch Canyon Open Space
URL:https://solanolandtrust.org/events-news/event-calendar.html/event/2026
 /04/25/nature-hike-at-lynch-canyon-april/559876
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
