DESCRIPTION:This April\, the streets will see something new – a parade o
 f larger-than-life moths\, migratory birds\, and other regional species. S
 anta Rosa artist-biologist Alina Nuebel\, the Santa Rosa Urban Arts Partne
 rship\, and community community partners\, with support from the City of S
 anta Rosa\, will be hosting the Earthly Procession – a parade to celebra
 te regional pride in our local natural environment\, raise awareness of th
 e environmental issues that are close to home\, and the tangible solutions
  that every person can implement for immediate results. Taking place in Sa
 nta Rosa’s underutilized bike and pedestrian infrastructure\, the Proces
 sion will be a joyous occupation of non-car spaces around downtown. Everyo
 ne is welcome to join\, and strongly encouraged to make or bring art of lo
 cal species. The Procession will meet at Juilliard Park at 12:00\, and wil
 l depart for Court House Square at 12:30. Once the parade arrives\, it wil
 l integrate with the Santa Rosa Earth Day Festival to display art and offe
 r interactive\, educational art activities.
