BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T180000
UID:260318mgP7_fk_AUCxLV_XsOYL8g
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\n**APRIL EXHIBIT: THE 
 POETIC LANDSCAPE**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\n*
 *RECEPTION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILL
 ER and PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by f
 eatured guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.
   Be sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beau
 tiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**\n\nSonoma
  County artist\, **Karen Miller\,** presents **The Poetic Landscape\,** pa
 stel paintings that convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting wi
 th the intrinsic beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid
  shapes and rhythmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true
  poetic interlude.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,”
  turning to the sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the
  river’s edge\, concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing
  in “Fetch.”  The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a 
 shaded secret spot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\,
  these works truly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Mill
 er remarked “ As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surroundin
 g us\, I try to express my painterly response in hopes it will engender re
 cognition by the viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting 
 the Gallery on March 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stai
 rway Smallworks Showcase features **Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\,** a c
 ollection of watercolors that create an atmosphere that is both introspect
 ive and magical.  Familiar domestic scenes are transformed as humans inte
 ract with animals and birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” 
 the red-headed young woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahe
 ad\, flanked by her avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like 
 taking a mini-step on the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nM
 eet the artist: Rapp will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 
 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nAlso join us for **ART NITE HEALDSBURG**\, Thursday\
 , April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.  The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets
  to Art.  ART NITE Healdsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is
  a community event celebrating art and creativity with over 20 galleries p
 articipating.  ArtNiteHealdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Cente
 r Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 
 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further information: Con
 tact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Javier Zamora in Conversation with Albert Flynn DeSilver
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T193000
UID:260314DJh8JjzJPkWo4SNfSgY2Hg
DESCRIPTION:The San Geronimo Valley Community Center\, in partnership with
  Canal Alliance and Book Passage\, is proud to present an evening with acc
 laimed poet and author Javier Zamora\, in conversation with poet\, memoir
 ist\, and educator Albert Flynn DeSilver\, on Saturday\, April 25 from
  6 – 7:30PM at the San Geronimo Valley Community Center.\n\nJavier Zam
 ora is widely celebrated for his powerful\, intimate writing that explores
  migration\, identity\, and belonging. Born in El Salvador\, Zamora came t
 o the United States by himself at the age of nine and later lived in the C
 anal District of San Rafael—an experience that profoundly shapes his wor
 k. His bestselling memoir\, Solito\, and his poetry have resonated with r
 eaders nationwide for their lyrical language and deeply human storytelling
 .\n\nIn this special event\, Zamora will be interviewed by Albert Flynn De
 Silver\, known for his dynamic presence and thoughtful\, wide-ranging conv
 ersations that invite both literary insight and personal reflection. Toget
 her\, they will explore Zamora’s creative process\, lived experience\, a
 nd the themes that animate his work.\n\nA Special Pre-Event Reception\n\nW
 e warmly invite you to upgrade for a special pre-event experience\, from 
 5:00–6:00pm\, which includes:\n\nA signed copy of Solito\n\nExclusive 
 time with Javier Zamora\n\nLight bites and festive beverages\n\nThe opport
 unity to connect with senior leaders from Canal Alliance and SGVCC\, along
  with fellow supporters\n\nThis experience is designed to bring you closer
  to the people\, stories\, and relationships that make this work possible 
 — and to celebrate the power of community-centered storytelling. Please 
 be sure to choose the “Pre-Event Reception” option at check out.\n\nTh
 is event is presented by Canal Alliance\, the San Geronimo Valley Communi
 ty Center and Book Passage\, organizations united by a shared commitment t
 o literacy\, community\, and cultural exchange\n\nSimultaneous English to 
 Spanish interpretation will be provided.\n\nJavier Zamora es reconocido po
 r su escritura poderosa e íntima que explora la migración\, la identidad
  y el sentido de pertenencia. Nacido en El Salvador\, Zamora llegó a los 
 Estados Unidos solo\, a los nueve años\, y vivió en el vecindario del Ca
 nal de San Rafael — experiencias que marcan su poesía y su exitoso libr
 o\, Solito. En este evento especial\, Zamora será entrevistado por Albert
  Flynn DeSilver\; juntos explorarán su proceso creativo\, su experiencia 
 de vida y los temas que dan forma a su obra.
LOCATION:San Geronimo Valley Community Center
URL:https://sgvperformingarts.eventcalendarapp.com/javier-zamora-in-conver
 sation-with-albert-flynn-desilver-a-literary-evening-at-the-san-geronimo-v
 alley-community-center
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
