BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Opera Film:  TURANDOT from Bregenz Festival
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T154500
UID:260113rckX3qy2gki0tRmIwDRfHw
DESCRIPTION:One of the world’s most famous arias comes from the
  composer’s final opera\, Turandot: “Nessun dorma” – none
  shall sleep because by morning the Chinese princess is determin
 ed to have discovered the name of the unknown  prince. The work
  is remarkable for its Chinese local color\, its opulent crowd 
 scenes\, its powerful choruses and its characters overwhelmed by 
 their emotions. Giacomo Puccini's masterpiece is 100 years old on
  04/25/26.  Celebrate with The Jarvis Conservatory by watching one of
  their favorite previous productions: Bregenz Festival - Seebühne
 . Projected with the latest in digital cinema technology.
LOCATION:Jarvis Conservatory
URL:https://jarvisconservatory.ticketspice.com/turandot-bregenz
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
