DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
UID:260401PHZTMNcz6U-c-XI5D7rXHw
DESCRIPTION:"Emergence" brings together the Artists of Fulton Crossing to 
 explore what Spring means to their creative lives. Spring is more than a s
 eason. It's a metaphor. It's renewal\, risk\, color\, thawing\, blooming\,
  awakening\, and sometimes even struggles. The public is invited to enjoy 
 this free Art exhibit and to take time to wander through the artists studi
 os and gallery spaces. Meet the artists at our opening reception March 21s
 t. Upcoming Art Workshops: March 21: Painting Easter Cookies. April 18: Ci
 gar Box Collage. May 16: Succulent Garden Centerpiece. Make treasures to b
 ring home. All ages welcome. Materials provided. E-mail Brenda at nanaspre
 ttypaper@outlook.com for preregistration and workshop info.
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/emergence-spring-through-the-eyes-of-
 the-artists/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"We The Sculptors…International Sculpture Days
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
UID:260331ukK1tXIn5k-O7QMucTX3RQ
DESCRIPTION:From ancient monuments carved in stone to bold contemporary ab
 straction\, sculpture has always been a defiant presence in the world. It 
 occupies space and refuses to be ignored.\n\nThis year’s International S
 culpture Days event embraces the belief that sculpture can inspire\, provo
 ke\, and challenge the world around us. Each artist will present their wor
 k \, and visitors can engage in acts of “defiant dissidence\,” explori
 ng how art can serve as both personal reflection and public voice.\n\nThe 
 event draws on a long tradition of artists and citizens using visual langu
 age to express dissent\, question norms\, and imagine new possibilities. A
 t its core\, *We The Sculptors* affirms the enduring role of artists to ch
 allenge\, to question\, and to stand visibly in the public square.
LOCATION:T Barny Gallery & Sculpture Garden
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/we-the-sculptors-intern
 ational-sculpture-days/18433856/2026-04-26T11
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Om For Peace
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T180000
UID:260331fcOOesdEfUK-T-Csx2xUTw
DESCRIPTION:Join us in praying for World Peace in 2026 using the meditativ
 e OM.\n\nNow is an important time to utilize the frequency of the Energy W
 ave Center plus our focused intentions\, for Peace in our communities\, ou
 rselves and our world. It’s a valuable window to help change course for 
 the better. More prayer now to strengthen possibilities for peace!\n\nThis
  event is a powerful Peace prayer and crystal bowl sound healing\, we hope
  you can join us!\n\nThings have changed since we first started OM Peace p
 rayers\, with Peace between India and Pakistan plus 5 other conflicts. We
 ’d like to see an end to the Ukraine-Russia conflict\, and continued Pea
 ce in the middle east. It’s all happening in this very moment.\n\nIn the
  2nd hour we direct the potent field created in the first through suggeste
 d visioning\, sharing dialog and a sound bath to help us all integrate. Co
 me join OM for Peace and lets Be The Change We Want to See in the World!\n
 \nAbout Your Guides\n\nEmile Canning is a Mediator & former owner of The I
 ntegratron. He is a pioneer in frequency healing and personal growth. Prod
 ucer of Peacewave Productions\, creator of uplifting & peaceful events thr
 oughout California.\n\nAnanda Fierro is an Advanced Bodyworker & Sound-Ene
 rgy Healer\, utilizing unique frequency medical devices to accelerate posi
 tive outcomes\, for over 2 decades. She studied with Jill Purce\, Sound & 
 Ancestral Healing pioneer in the UK.
LOCATION:Energy Wave Center
URL:https://energywavecenter.com/om-for-peace/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:INTO THE LIGHT: Light-filled aintings by Katy Boggs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T170000
UID:2603301wvmk-anhEqT6B5wv5MetA
DESCRIPTION:Katy's paintings are an exploration of light—how it shapes f
 orm\, reveals color\, and defines what we see.\n\n"I am drawn to moments w
 here light is felt as much as seen: filtering through dense leaves\, tower
 ing in the crowns of trees\, glinting off cresting waves\, or softening in
 to the quiet glow of a sunset. Light is everywhere\; without it\, there is
  no seeing. Beyond its physical presence\, it also carries a deeper resona
 nce as a symbol of hope. In a time of uncertainty\, this work seeks to bri
 ng light into the image\, both visually and metaphorically."\n\nReception:
  April 25\, 4 to 6 pm.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Gallery
URL:http://sebastopolgallery.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
