BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Exploring Botanical Monotypes
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T170000
UID:260328GdlitKDJ9ku64gEyDdUGYA
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSunday\, April 26\, 2026 11:00 AM – 5:00 PM\n\nE
 xperience Level\n\nBeginning\n\nEvent Category: Printmaking\n\nAge\\(s\\)\
 n\n18 and older\n\n$140 – Registration Cost $25 – Materials Fee $165 
 – Total Registration Cost\n\nCreate stunning botanical monotype prints w
 ith spring foliage in this inspiring workshop—perfect for beginners and 
 plant lovers alike!\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nLearn to make stunning\, one-of
 -a-kind botanical prints inspired from the natural world! Join Kelly in th
 is one-day experimental monotype printmaking workshop where you will explo
 re techniques on the printing press. Students will learn how to achieve un
 ique color compositions using local flora as stencils through simple layer
 ing and masking in a supportive group learning environment. Guests are inv
 ited to print using a wide variety of spring foliage and preserved botanic
 als. Kelly will also discuss and demonstrate how to add dimension to print
 s by using textures\, mixed media and collage. It is sure to be a fun and 
 awe-inspiring class for beginners or even experienced printmakers interest
 ed in learning a beautiful new technique. If you love plants\, and you’v
 e always wanted to try monotype\, this class is sure to motivate and inspi
 re you!\n\nMembership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above
  receive 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase over $40. Ma
 terials fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find communi
 ty\, connection\, and creativity.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/exploring-botanical-monotyp
 es/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
