BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T170000
UID:2603249aLy2ZRwlE6dvUGgXh5Z0Q
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts (HCA) invites
  artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mixed 
 media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry for th
 is exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n\\- Platform: All applicati
 ons must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n\\- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n\\- Size/Weight:
  Artwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed (144 sq in) or 196 sq in frame
 d. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n\\- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired (no alligator clips). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are responsib
 le for on-site assembly if required.\n\n\\- Sales: All work must be for sa
 le. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list retail
  prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n\\- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 (9 PM)\n\
 n\\- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n\\- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 (must include pre-paid return label)\n\n\\-
  Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 (12–4 PM) and Monday\, June 1 (11 AM–1
  PM)\n\n\\- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n\\- Open
 ing Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 (4–6 PM)\n\n\\- Pick-up/Return S
 hipping: July 19 (12–4 PM) and July 20 (11 AM–1 PM)\; shipping the wee
 k of July 20.\n\nEntry Fees:\n\n\\- Non-Members: $50 (1 entry)\, $55 (2 en
 tries)\, $60 (3 entries). Includes a $60 yearly supporter membership.\n\n\
 \- Current Members: $40 (1 entry)\, $45 (2 entries)\, $50 (3 entries).
LOCATION:Healdsburg Center for the Arts
URL:https://healdsburgcenterforthearts.org/small-wonders-2/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Edible & Medicinal Plant Walk
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T130000
UID:260319ybgvgHngTkeWclF9jxQMDw
DESCRIPTION:Weaving in natural history\, ethnobotany\, herbalism and
  folktales\, this walk will open your senses\, as well as your
  curiosity to the abundance of plantlore in Sonoma County.\n\nTic
 kets are $15 for adults\, $7.5 for youth (12-17 year olds\; all
  children under 18 must be accompanied by a parent or legal gu
 ardian)\, students\, Sugarloaf members\, and Sugarloaf or RFO volu
 nteers\, and free for children under 12. Meet at the White Barn
  parking lot. Bring at least a quart of water and a lunch and
  be prepared for a leisurely 2-3 mile walk with a 250-ft climb
 . Wear layers\, appropriate footwear for slippery (and possibly m
 uddy) terrain\, and sun protection. Heavy rains cancel\; parking 
 fees apply.\n\nEdible plant information is for educational purposes
  only. Foraging is illegal in CA State Parks.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/edmedplantsap2026
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Patron Saints of Influence Spring Reading & Open Mic
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T180000
UID:260319_AwZmSC_3kKuTVlCoF0rDQ
DESCRIPTION:The next Patron Saints of Influence quarterly literary reading
  & open mic on Sunday\, April 26 will pay homage to the poet\, musician\, 
 and political activist **Gil Scott-Heron** with featured readings by **Yum
 e Kim**\, **Steve Shain**\, and **Grayson Thompson**. Find us at Shady Oak
  Barrel House in Santa Rosa starting at 4PM.\n\nAs always\, you are also w
 elcome to share some of your own written work in 5 minutes or less during 
 the open mic (arrive early to sign up). That could include song lyrics or 
 spoken word if you're especially inspired by Gil Scott-Heron\, but all wor
 ds are welcome as long as they're not hateful.\n\n**About the Featured Rea
 ders:**\n\n**Yume Kim** is a poet\, educator\, and author of *Reserve the 
 Right*. In 2011\, she moved from her home state Virginia to California for
  her graduate studies at San Francisco State University. There\, she earne
 d both an M.A. in English and an M.F.A. in Creative Writing. Additionally\
 , she is a recipient of the following fellowships: Kundiman (June 2012)\, 
 The Ruby Creatives in Residence (2022-2023)\, and The Bay Area Writing Pro
 ject Invitational Summer Institute (June 2024). Some of her works can also
  be found in the following journals: *gesture*\, *sPARKLE + bLINK*\, *West
  Wind Review*\, *Transfer*\, S*ugared Water*\, *Writing Without Walls*\, *
 The Bangalore Review*\, *You Might Need to Hear This*\, and *The Sad Girls
  Lit Club*.\n\n**Steve Shain**'s journey with the voice of the bass began 
 in 1963 in Chicago Heights\, Ill. Since being introduced to beat generatio
 n poet ruth weiss by painter Paul Beattie in 1984\, Steve has usually been
  seen accompanying poets throughout the Bay Area. Most recently\, Steve’
 s own verbiage is being shared\; a unique/personal perspective on a life l
 ived\, from a survivor/observer/commentator. The voice of Steve’s bass i
 s special\, too: a 1930s Alcoa made in Buffalo\, NY\, Dura (the bass) spea
 ks: not jazz/not classical/not bluegrass but “BASSICNESS” … inherent
  tones & rhythms dictated by inspiration and the present tense. His teache
 rs include Florence Dangermond\, Nancy McCain\, Edward Krolick\, Curtis Bu
 rris\, and Glen Moore. His muse-ical mentors include Ron Crotty\, Darrell 
 DeVore\, Richard Waters\, and Harry Partch. He has also shared stages with
  ruth weiss\, Jack Micheline\, Lawrence Ferlinghetti\, Eugene Ruggles\, Sh
 errill Milnes\, Eugene Istomin\, Earl LeClaire\, and David Best\; and reco
 rded with Leopard Set\, Tom Waits\, and others. When not playing bass\, St
 eve can be found as proprietor of “bassic sewing”\, a Santa Rosa leath
 er fabrication & repair shop.\n\n**Grayson Thompson** \\[he/him\\] is a Bl
 ack\, Jamaican-American\, queer transgender cowboy poet who moonlights as 
 a therapist. He is the inaugural Slam Poetry Champion of Santa Rosa\, CA. 
 A mouthful\, Grayson is Foglifter Press' 2024 Start A Riot! Chapbook Prize
  Winner with *SAND BODIED FLORIDA BOY* and Winner of Write Bloody Publishi
 ng's 2024 Jack McCarthy Book Prize for his full-length collection\, *A CON
 GREGATION OF ALLIGATORS* (September 2025). Born in Massachusetts\, raised 
 between Florida and New England\, Grayson’s work centers the body and it
 s relationship to the prerequisites needed for social existence…to be re
 cognized by others as being human. His poems explore race\, queerness\, an
 d gender\; family\, grief\, and grace.
LOCATION:Shady Oak Barrel House
URL:http://tinyurl.com/patron-saints-form
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T180000
UID:260318mCCF2fP_tUS4yTmTgnCExg
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\n**APRIL EXHIBIT: THE 
 POETIC LANDSCAPE**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\n*
 *RECEPTION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILL
 ER and PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by f
 eatured guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.
   Be sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beau
 tiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**\n\nSonoma
  County artist\, **Karen Miller\,** presents **The Poetic Landscape\,** pa
 stel paintings that convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting wi
 th the intrinsic beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid
  shapes and rhythmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true
  poetic interlude.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,”
  turning to the sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the
  river’s edge\, concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing
  in “Fetch.”  The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a 
 shaded secret spot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\,
  these works truly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Mill
 er remarked “ As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surroundin
 g us\, I try to express my painterly response in hopes it will engender re
 cognition by the viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting 
 the Gallery on March 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stai
 rway Smallworks Showcase features **Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\,** a c
 ollection of watercolors that create an atmosphere that is both introspect
 ive and magical.  Familiar domestic scenes are transformed as humans inte
 ract with animals and birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” 
 the red-headed young woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahe
 ad\, flanked by her avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like 
 taking a mini-step on the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nM
 eet the artist: Rapp will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 
 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nAlso join us for **ART NITE HEALDSBURG**\, Thursday\
 , April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.  The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets
  to Art.  ART NITE Healdsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is
  a community event celebrating art and creativity with over 20 galleries p
 articipating.  ArtNiteHealdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Cente
 r Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 
 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further information: Con
 tact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
