BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:SUP Yoga on the Petaluma River
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T110000
UID:260317RwBlOpx3ZUiyrr64-fLcTQ
DESCRIPTION:Slow down and float into a quieter rhythm with SUP Yoga on the
  Petaluma River at The Floathouse Petaluma. Launching from downtown Petalu
 ma\, this peaceful on-the-water yoga experience feels worlds away from the
  bustle—set in the calm\, protected turning basin where the river natura
 lly invites you to relax.\n\nThis all-levels\, 90-minute session welcomes 
 everyone\, from first-time paddle boarders and yoga newcomers to experienc
 ed practitioners. We begin with a short\, gentle paddle from the docks to 
 get comfortable on your board \\(knees are always welcome\\)\, then anchor
  together so tidal movement won’t interrupt your flow. Once settled\, yo
 u’re free to move\, stretch\, rest\, or simply be—guided by expert ins
 truction and supported by the shared energy of the group. Evening sessions
  and morning sessions allow YOU to choose the vibe that suits you best.\n\
 nAll equipment is provided\, including extra-stable paddleboards that are 
 wider and longer than a yoga mat\, designed to help you feel grounded and 
 secure on the water.\n\nPerfect for locals and Bay Area visitors alike\, S
 UP Yoga on the Petaluma River offers a rare chance to experience downtown 
 Petaluma from the water—peaceful\, playful\, and deeply restorative.\n\n
 It’s YOUR river. Come out and play.
LOCATION:The Floathouse Petaluma
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/sup-yoga-on-the-petalum
 a-river/18069218/2026-04-26T09
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Brandlin Estate Wine & Food Tasting Experience
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
UID:260312yQdlVt2sMEuujce96iTmqw
DESCRIPTION:Born on the rugged slopes of Mount Veeder\, Brandlin Estate pr
 oduces wines of structure\, intensity\, and place. The Brandlin Experience
  offers an in-depth exploration of this historic vineyard site through a c
 urated tasting of five estate-grown wines—including Zinfandel from centu
 ry-old vines and the estate’s signature Cabernet Sauvignon. This seated\
 , guided experience invites guests to delve into the mountain terroir thro
 ugh the lens of small-lot winemaking. Each wine reflects the elevation\, e
 xposure\, and rocky soils that define the Brandlin Estate. For an added di
 mension\, guests may opt to include seasonal bites\, thoughtfully paired t
 o complement the structure and complexity of the wines. This experience is
  hosted at the picturesque Boathouse.
LOCATION:Brandlin Estate 
URL:https://www.exploretock.com/brandlinestate/experience/565565/the-brand
 lin-wine-food-tasting-experience?date=2026-03-12&size=2&time=10%3A00
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
