BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Park Rx—Forest Bathing Walks 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T130000
UID:260227B8oPeS7JOkq7jrN7Mwe5gA
DESCRIPTION:Have you heard about “Shinrin-yoku” or “forest ba
 thing”? Here is an opportunity to take a walk and experience 
 the practice for yourself. Learn techniques to maximize the healt
 h benefits and stress reducing qualities of this walking practice
 . Shinrin-yoku originated in Japan and is gaining popularity in 
 the United States for its documented health benefits. This practi
 ce takes a walk in the woods to another level. A centering and
  calming restorative practice\, it promotes balance and restored 
 vitality through a quality of presence and heightened sensory awa
 reness. Sugarloaf Ridge State Park hosts a Forest Therapy Series
  as part of its Park Rx Program the 4th Sunday of the month 
 (March through November) led by certified Association of Nature a
 nd Forest Therapy (ANFT) practitioners.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/2026forestbathing
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Overeaters Anonymous (OA) Newcomer Meeting in Santa Rosa
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T170000
UID:260212AcH96JXIYE-9mUZ2i2SAng
DESCRIPTION:**Is Food a Problem for You? You Are Not Alone.**\n\nOvereater
 s Anonymous (OA) is a fellowship of people who support each other in recov
 ering from compulsive eating and food behaviors. If you feel you have a pr
 oblem with food\, OA welcomes you—no matter what your background\, belie
 fs\, or eating habits.\n\nWe hold an in-person newcomer meeting on **Sunda
 ys from 4:00 – 5:00 PM** **at Christ Church United Methodist\, 1717 Yulu
 pa Ave.\, Room #4\, Santa Rosa**. Contact: Abigail (707) 293-5888. You may
  view all North Bay OA in-person and online meetings at https://www.northb
 ayoa.org/meetings.html .\n\nIn OA\, members experience **spiritual\, emoti
 onal\, and physical recovery** by practicing the **Twelve Steps** and livi
 ng by their spiritual principles—one day at a time.\n\nOA is **not** a d
 iet club or calorie-counting program.\n\nMembers have different plans of e
 ating.\n\nOA does **not** endorse any specific food plan.\n\nIf food is ca
 using problems in your life\, you don’t have to struggle alone. Recovery
  is possible\, and help is available.\n\n**Visit:** https://www.northbayoa
 .org/\n\n**Find a meeting:** https://www.northbayoa.org/meetings.html
LOCATION:Christ Church United Methodist
URL:https://www.northbayoa.org/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
