DESCRIPTION:The speakers for this talk will be Dan Ryan with Redwood Credi
 t Union\, an AI expert\, Crista Barnett with Senior Advocacy Services Nort
 h Bay\, and Amanda Esposti\, the Windsor Police Dept Community Services Of
 ficer. Using examples\, they will give you tips on how to recognize AI gen
 erated material\, scams\, and elder abuse\, plus provide tips on what to d
 o to protect yourself. Amanda will wrap up the talk to let you know what W
 indsor Police Dept has seen lately in our area. A car safety hammer is inc
 luded\, while supplies last\, one per family. The talk is free for all to 
 attend\, so please share this invite.\n\nTo register go to https://bit.ly/
 ScamsAISeminar or call the Senior Center at 707-838-1260. Pre-registration
  is not required but is recommended for the Car Safety Hammer giveaway. Fo
 r those of you who don’t drive\, there will be an alternative giveaway. 
 This presentation is part of the Windsor Ready Talk series hosted by the T
 own of Windsor and Windsor COPE. For more information email windsor\\_cope
 @yahoo.com.
LOCATION:Windsor Senior Center
URL:https://bit.ly/ScamsAISeminar
