 kins\,  ahopkins@santarosa.edu Guided experiments teach students how diffe
 rent mixed media materials work and what effects they create. Use a variet
 y of acrylic mediums\, papers\, collage\, ink\, pastel\, rice paper\, fabr
 ic and more. Add depth and visual interest to paintings with dimensional t
 extures and learn how to incorporate interesting collage materials. Just t
 he right blend of structure and play with an attitude of openness encourag
 es creative freedom. SRJC offers noncredit courses for seniors as part of 
 its goal to provide lifelong learning. For information on joining a class 
 please visit: https://lifelong.santarosa.edu/ No age limit for SRJC Lifelo
 ng Learning courses\, though they are tailored for seniors. Students may r
 egister at any time during the semester. No fee for SRJC Lifelong Learning
  courses. Contact Instructor for enrollment details\,  ahopkins@santarosa.
 edu The Sonoma County Junior College District does not discriminate on the
  basis of race\, religious creed\, color\, national origin\, ancestry\, et
