BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spooky Book Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260429T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260429T180000
UID:260102M_AtOshOfk20VG_yFEC6NA
DESCRIPTION:Spooky Book Club meets at 6pm on the last Wednesday of each mo
 nth. Read any novel\, novella\, graphic novel\, etc. that fits the monthly
  theme and join us for great conversation and community.\n\nTHEMES\n\nJanu
 ary\n\nMonsters & Creatures: Vampires\, werewolves\, demons\, cryptids\, 
 or anything non-human and terrifying. \n\nFebruary\n\nFolk Horror & Urban 
 Legends: Curses\, rituals\, superstition\, isolated communities\, local m
 yths.\n\nMarch\n\nSurvivor’s Guilt: Survivors\, slashers\, killer-on-th
 e-loose stories.\n\nApril\n\nPsychological Terror: Unreliable narrators\,
  paranoia\, mind games\, and slow-burn dread.\n\nMay\n\nHaunted Places: G
 hosts\, cursed houses\, abandoned buildings\, restless spirits.\n\nJune\n\
 nWeird Fiction & Cosmic Horror: Eldritch vibes\, the unknowable\, reality
 -bending strangeness\n\nJuly\n\nBody Horror: Transformation\, disease\, m
 edical terror\, the uncanny in flesh.\n\nAugust\n\nDark Academia: Creepy 
 campuses\, secret societies\, intellectual obsession.\n\nSeptember\n\nEco-
 Horror & Nature Strikes Back: Creatures\, plants\, or environmental force
 s turning hostile.\n\nOctober\n\nSupernatural Thrillers: Possessions\, ex
 orcisms\, occult forces\, or mysterious powers.\n\nNovember\n\nInternation
 al Horror: Any horror written by or set in another country/culture.\n\nDe
 cember\n\nGothic Classics & Modern Gothics: Old mansions\, family secrets
 \, brooding atmosphere\, gothic romance elements.
LOCATION:Vallejo John F. Kennedy Library
URL:https://solanolibrary.libnet.info/event/15294871
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
