BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Drawing in Joy: Laughing with Life\, a Dance on Paper
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T200000
UID:260324xELyOW6ytEOneOCiKglJXw
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nThursdays\, April 9 – 30\, 2026 5:30 PM – 8:00
  PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Cat
 egories: Drawing & Painting\, Extended Classes\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and old
 er\n\nRegistration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nMaterials Fee:\n\nSee Required List\n\
 nTotal Registration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nExpress joy through drawing. Build sk
 ills in sketching\, composition & landscapes. Boost focus\, creativity\, c
 onnection & well-being.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nWhen we feel a sense of joy\
 , it is natural to express that feeling from our body. We may use our voic
 e and sing\, we may dance\, and we may use our hands in creative expressio
 n. By drawing we leave a mark of that expression. This course is shaped wi
 th skill building exercises to improve eye-hand coordination with quick sk
 etching and gesture drawing and practices of learning to see how to abstra
 ct shapes of light and dark for developing strong compositions. We will fo
 cus on landscape imagery from photos and drawing from setups in the studio
 . Drawing outside of class will be encouraged but not required. There are 
 many health benefits from drawing such as: improvements in cognitive focus
 \, freedom of expression with your hands\, the satisfaction that comes fro
 m seeing the world in a different way\, the social camaraderie of acceptan
 ce in the studio\, and the joy of doing something with your hands.\n\nRequ
 ired Materials List\n\nA good size sketch book for multimedia\n\nNewsprint
  drawing pad \\(12” x 18” or 18” x 24”\\)\n\nBlack pencils\, 6B so
 ft\n\nCompressed charcoal sticks\, black and white\n\nEraser\, kneaded rub
 ber\n\nEraser\, white vinyl\n\nBlack felt pens
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/drawing-in-joy/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T170000
UID:260324hbcfl2JOy0qZ3Wjp7vMV0g
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts (HCA) invites
  artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mixed 
 media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry for th
 is exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n\\- Platform: All applicati
 ons must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n\\- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n\\- Size/Weight:
  Artwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed (144 sq in) or 196 sq in frame
 d. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n\\- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired (no alligator clips). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are responsib
 le for on-site assembly if required.\n\n\\- Sales: All work must be for sa
 le. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list retail
  prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n\\- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 (9 PM)\n\
 n\\- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n\\- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 (must include pre-paid return label)\n\n\\-
  Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 (12–4 PM) and Monday\, June 1 (11 AM–1
  PM)\n\n\\- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n\\- Open
 ing Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 (4–6 PM)\n\n\\- Pick-up/Return S
 hipping: July 19 (12–4 PM) and July 20 (11 AM–1 PM)\; shipping the wee
 k of July 20.\n\nEntry Fees:\n\n\\- Non-Members: $50 (1 entry)\, $55 (2 en
 tries)\, $60 (3 entries). Includes a $60 yearly supporter membership.\n\n\
 \- Current Members: $40 (1 entry)\, $45 (2 entries)\, $50 (3 entries).
LOCATION:Healdsburg Center for the Arts
URL:https://healdsburgcenterforthearts.org/small-wonders-2/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
